title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers for three days in pickling salt and water. Drain.
Soak in ice water two days changing water both days, then drain.
Simmer (one hour or more until pickles are clear) in water and 1 Tbsp. alum.
Rinse and drain well.

title: apricot delight
directions: Prepare Jell-O using hot water.
Do not add cold water.
Add canned fruit, juice and all; prepare pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over Jell-O.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: three bean soup
directions: Cook ham bone with potatoes until potatoes are done.
Add peas and all beans, juice and all to the ham and potato pot.
Saute floured onions in butter; add to soup mixture.
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup All-Bran with boiling water.
Cool.
Add oil. Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients together.
Stir in 2 remaining cups of bran and the first bran mixture.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake 18 minutes at 400°.
Makes 24.

title: "nana palma's" manicotti
directions: Note:
You can also use this as a crepe recipe and fill with your favorite preserve!

title: shrimp salad mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin with tomato soup.
Heat to dissolve.
Cool. Soften cream cheese with milk and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice and stir into soup mixture.
Fold in remaining ingredients and fill fish mold or shell mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix into cakes and fry.
Cheese can also be melted over these after they are browned.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; if not enough to make 2 cups, finish with water.
Add juice of one lemon and bring to a boil. Dissolve gelatine in a little water and add to cooked juices, then add sugar, a little at a time.
Cook a few minutes more over low heat, then chill.
After it jells, add oranges, apples, pineapple, nuts and whipped cream.
Mix together and refrigerate.

title: wacky cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: stuffed peppers with creole sauce
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cut tops from peppers. Remove membranes and seeds. Cover peppers with boiling water. Cook 10 minutes and drain. Brown ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper in skillet. Add salt and rice. Spoon mixture into peppers. Place in baking dish and pour following Creole Sauce over peppers. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer. "Delicious."

title: molasses baked chicken(serves 2)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine molasses, corn syrup, soy sauce, lemon and white wine in bowl.
Stir to blend.
Dip chicken in mixture and put in greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Pour mixture over top.
Sprinkle top with sesame seed.
Bake 30 minutes, basting frequently.
Add bananas, rolling in sauce to coat.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve sauce over chicken and bananas.

title: homemade chicken and dumplings
directions: Knead together.
Roll out dough and cut into squares.
Cook desired amount of chicken until done; leaving enough broth in pan to cook dumplings.
Add dumplings and cook until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Place chicken breasts in bottom.
Layer cheese over these.
Mix soup and water and pour over cheese.
Add herbed dressing and drizzle butter over top.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350° covered.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Top with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in thin strips, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Turn in flour, brown in butter.
Saute onion and mushrooms, add soup and cook on low heat an hour.
Add sour cream the last 5 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all together.
Set in refrigerator overnight for flavors to blend.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Cream together vanilla, sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Place cookies flat side down in wrappers.
Drop glob of mixture on cookie so cup is about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or more.
When cool, top with pie filling or fresh fruit.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix well beaten eggs, pumpkin, Eagle Brand milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top in order with dry cake mix, pecans and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool.
Cut into squares and top with Cool Whip.

title: pralines
directions: Have boiling water ready in case you need to soften candy. Mix first 4 ingredients; bring to boil.
Test for soft ball in cold water.
When soft ball stage reached, add vanilla.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Then beat until creamy.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a greased casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour beef balls
directions: Mix together the beef, egg, salt, pepper, green onions and 1 tablespoon of cornstarch.
Shape into marble size balls.
Drain pineapple, reserving the juice.
Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in skillet and brown meat balls on all sides.
Remove.
Add remaining cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, water and pineapple juice. Add to skillet, stirring steadily until thickened.
Add pineapple, green peppers and meat balls.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: tasty salmonettes
directions: Drain juice from salmon, set aside.
Put salmon in mixing bowl and stir in the egg.
When it is gummy, add 1/2 cup flour.
Stir thoroughly.
Mixture will be thick.
Do not add any salt or pepper. Take 1/4 cup salmon juice (pour out excess) and add heaping teaspoonful baking powder; beat with a fork until it foams to 3/4 cup of measuring cup.
After foaming process, pour into salmon mixture.
Mix again with fork.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil. They will turn themselves over.
Drain on paper towel.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in 3 cups of grated carrots.
Divide batter into 3 layer pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: congealed mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges. Reserve juices. Add enough water to juices to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin in hot tea. Add 1 1/2 cups reserved liquid and chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and water chestnuts.
Spoon mixture into a lightly oiled 6-cup ring mold. Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold onto a lettuce lined plate. Line center with lettuce.
Spoon small portion of dressing in center and garnish, if desired. Serve remaining dressing on the side.
Yields 8 servings.

title: orange pineapple frost
directions: Mix jello and undrained pineapple.
Add marshmallows and mandarin oranges.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup in a 2-quart casserole. Microwave on 100% power for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts. Microwave on 100% power for 5 minutes.
Peanuts and syrup will be light brown.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water, salt, and vinegar to boil.

title: mom's slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, 2/3 cup of oil or bacon drippings and oil to make 2/3 cup.
Chill.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour,
salt and pepper.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Add broth or water and egg.
Makes a soft dough.
Divide into two parts and roll our very thin and cut into strips.
Let dry at least 15 minutes.
Cut into small squares and drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cook until tender.

title: orange slice nut cake
directions: Cut dates, pecans and orange slices into small pieces.
Add coconut.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
In another bowl, cream the eggs and sugar.
Add flour, soda and buttermilk and mix well.
Pour over nut mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until almost "set." Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until firm.
Serves 10.

title: grandmother's lemon pie(1930)
directions: Cream all ingredients together with 1/2 stick butter.
Then add 2 cups boiling water and cook in a double boiler.
Boil until thick and pour into a pie shell.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool and top with fruit.
Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter; add ground beef and heat, but do not brown.
Season.
Spread 3 cups cabbage in a 2-quart casserole baking dish.
Cover with meat and onion mixture.
Top with meat and onion mixture.
Top with remaining cabbage.
Pour can of tomato soup over top.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 350°.
(May also use chopped green pepper if you like.)

title: popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
A 2-quart pitcher works well for pouring into muffin tins.
Pour batter into greased tin (glass or cast-iron works best) about halfway.
Put in cold oven on 450° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 10.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion, butter and rice in saucepan until lightly brown. Add 1 can of mushroom soup and, using the soup can, add 1 can of water.
Add bouillon.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Crush enough to make 1 cup. Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water and berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
(The mixture should be thickened.)

title: coq au vin
directions: Dredge chicken	pieces	in
flour; saute until brown in melted butter.
Combine
lemon
juice, wine, mushrooms, broth and seasoning in
a deep oven pot.
Add chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.	Serve with cooked rice.

title: best bread ever
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Mix together sugar, salt, milk, 3 cups water, shortening and 6 cups of flour.
Stir rapidly to get a smooth batter.
Add remaining flour.
Let rise twice, punching down in between.
Add more flour if needed.
The more you knead and punch the dough, the better the bread.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell.
(If using metal or foil pan, bake on preheated heavy-duty baking sheet.)
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack. Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple-orange danish toast
directions: Mix the cheese, pineapple, marmalade and cinnamon; then spread on toast.
Place under broiler and heat until bubbly.
Makes 1 serving (249 cal; 64% carbohydrate, 20% fat, 16% protein).

title: five hour stew
directions: Place stew in casserole or crock-pot.
Sprinkle dry soup over meat.
Pour in mushroom soup.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours, or in crock-pot, use high heat for 30 minutes, then low for 4 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased wide-mouth glass canning pint jars.
Fill "Ball" brand jars 1/3 full.
Fill "Kerr" brand jars 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
When done, remove one jar at a time from oven.
Clean sealing edge and screw lid tight.
Yields 9 "Kerr" jars.
Safe to keep on the shelf for 6 months.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Stir in 2 cups flour to which salt has been added.
Add 2 cups lukewarm water and 4 1/2 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Flour board and knead thoroughly.
Set aside to rise or put in refrigerator until needed.
Remove from refrigerator and knead again.
Roll and cut like biscuits.
Let rise for 4 to 5 hours.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut and let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well. Add milk, coconut mixture and vanilla.
Pour in 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 350° until center is set.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Sift salt, baking powder and soda with 1 cup of flour, add to mix. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out very thin.
Cut out and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: bean pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper and put in bottom of a casserole dish.
Put drained beans on top of beef and layer chopped tomatoes.
Then pour tomato paste and 1/2 can water over top.
Place grated cheese over mixture.
Mix Mexican corn bread by directions on package and spoon on top of mixture.
Cook on 375° to 400° oven until brown.

title: reuben bake
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan; add water to cover and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until very tender; drain well.
Combine potatoes, sour cream and the next 3 ingredients in a bowl and beat at medium speed of a mixer for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Set aside.

title: molasses oatmeal bread
directions: In saucepan, bring 2 cups water to boil.
Gradually stir in oats.
Cook, stirring, until thick (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat; add salt, molasses and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast over 1 cup lukewarm water in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm molasses mixture and 3 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Gradually add remaining flour, mixing with hands.
Knead for 10 to 12 minutes, adding more flour if needed.

title: deviled eggs(kid's stuff)
directions: Boil 9 eggs in water for 10 hours and then crack them open. Get that yellow yolk out.
Add a little water to yolk and then put the eggs in the shells.
Then put paprika on top.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small bowl.
Set aside 1/2 cup of mixture for dredging fruit.
Combine pecans, pineapple, dates and cherries in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Dredge fruit mixture in 1/2 cup reserved flour mixture.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 in loaf pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, milk and margarine over low heat.
Pour on baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top of caramel mixture.
Pour rest of cake mix over this and return to oven; bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn relish
directions: Precook the corn 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool and cut from cob.
Chop other vegetables.
Mix together.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 25 minutes.
Pour into cans and seal.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Melt butter or oleo; add garlic.
Lightly season chicken with salt and pepper, then brush on butter mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: southwestern cheese dip
directions: Place cheeses in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Top with bacon, onions and chilies.	Microwave at 50% power for 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring every 2 minutes. Serve with vegetables or chips.
Yields 3 cups.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix Velveeta cheese, cream cheese, onion and garlic salt in a bowl with hands.
Shape into logs, like rolls. Make about 4 log rolls.
After shaping, set aside.
Using wax paper, place 1 cup pecans on paper with desired amount of chili powder. Take cheese rolls and roll over and over in nuts and chili powder until well covered.
Serve on Hi Ho crackers.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet lightly.
Cover with stewed tomatoes. Mix soup mix with reserved tomato juice and water.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Can serve with rice or noodles.

title: dressing for green salad
directions: Mix together. This keeps very well in the refrigerator.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Pour pineapple into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour blueberry pie filling on top; sprinkle dry cake mix over berries.
Melt margarine; drizzle over cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake until crispy brown in a 350° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar.
Add eggs, corn syrup and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: date cake
directions: Put water and dates in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Add soda. Set aside to cool.
Cream together shortening and sugar. Add rest of ingredients, date mixture last.

title: asparagus-blue cheese roll-ups
directions: With a rolling pin, roll the bread slices flat.
Beat together Blue cheese, cream cheese, egg and mayonnaise.
Spread on bread slices.
Lay an asparagus spear on each and roll up jelly roll style.
Cut each roll into 3 pieces, using a very sharp knife. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with caraway seeds, if desired.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve hot.
These may be prepared in advance and refrigerated or frozen, then baked at serving time.
Makes 45 or more roll-ups.

title: banana split
directions: Mix and press in 12 x 9-inch pan and bake until lightly brown at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.
Great for raw vegetables, sharp apples.

title: puree of turnips and potatoes
directions: Boil the turnips and potatoes in water to cover until very soft; drain.
Keep warm.
Saute the onion in 2 tablespoons butter until softened and very lightly browned.
Combine the onion with the turnips, potatoes and 1/4 cup milk.
Mash until almost smooth, adding more butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Whip until very smooth with an electric mixer, adding more milk if you desire a thinner consistency.
Lightly butter the top.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Add 2 cups uncooked rice.
Simmer two hours, stirring.

title: almond holiday rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Set aside.
In a medium skillet, saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add almonds, pimentos, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Fold in cooked rice.
Fold mixture into an oiled, 2-quart baking dish.
Pour whipping cream over rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Serves 6.

title: corn chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and water; cook until tender.
Do not drain.
Add margarine, cream-style corn and whole kernel corn. Add milk last.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Add cooking oil, eggs, applesauce and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together with an electric mixer; do not overmix.
Stir in walnuts, if desired.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until done.
As all ovens may vary, I bake about 55 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: parmesan toast strips
directions: Mix
corn flake
crumbs
and
Parmesan	cheese.
Remove crusts from toast slices;	cut
each
into
narrow
strips. Combine margarine and onion
salt.	Roll
strips in margarine, then in crumb mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° about 5 minutes or until crisp.
Better served slightly warmed. Makes approximately 25.

title: salmon spread
directions: Shape into ball and chill.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm Party Rumpers.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into two balls and roll each in pecans and parsley.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: strawberries on the square
directions: Arrange 9 crackers in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package for pudding.
Fold in 1 cup topping.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers in pan; top with strawberries.
Arrange remaining 9 crackers on berries.
Add remaining pudding mixture.
Spread remaining whipped topping over all.
Garnish with additional strawberries, if desired.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: best ever corn bread dressing
directions: For a delicious change, substitute large bell pepper or 4 to 6 stalks celery

title: special cornbread
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Add cornmeal and baking powder.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned in an 8 or 9-inch skillet.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook hamburg, onion, pepper and bacon and drain.
Do not drain the beans.
Mix all together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Mix brown sugar and water.
Add to cranberry juice and pineapple juice.
Pour into percolator.
In top of percolator, place 2 sticks cinnamon and 2 whole cloves.
Perk through cycle.

title: peanut brittle # 2
directions: Combine sugar and syrup with 1/2 cup water in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring mixture to boil, then add butter.
Stir frequently until mixture reaches 230° on a candy thermometer.
Add raw peanuts and continue stirring until temperature reaches 305°. Remove from heat and quickly stir in baking soda.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Filling:
In medium saucepan, cook onion, parsley, nutmeg and pepper in hot oil.
Cover over low heat.
When onion is tender, stir in dill and set aside.
In medium bowl, combine eggs and milk; beat with mixer until smooth.
Add onion mixture, spinach and Feta.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken biscuit pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove skin and bones.
Save stock and dice chicken.
Combine chicken, peas, carrots and celery.
Add flour to stock to thicken.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Place in casserole. Top with biscuit dough and cook at 450° until biscuits are brown. Makes 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all other ingredients and fold in broccoli.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Chop 1 cup berries.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Add chopped strawberries; cook stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cool in refrigerator 1/2 hour.
Pour 3 /4 of mixture in pie crust.
Stand up remaining berries in pie mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over berries.
Chill until firm about 3 hours.
Serve with cool whip.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Line baking pan with aluminum foil long enough to seal. Spray bottom
with Pam or grease lightly.
Wash chicken parts and
dry thoroughly.
Dip chicken parts into egg or milk (salt and pepper added), then roll in crumbs and place in foil-lined pan,
skin side
down.
Do
not
let parts touch.
Seal foil. Bake
in
oven for 1 hour, then open foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: empanadas
directions: Brown meat and other ingredients, except pastry.
Cook until done.
If too thin, add flour to thicken.
Cut pastry in circles; put meat in half the circle.
Fold over; press edges together. Brush with milk.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes.

title: carlson's shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave, approximately 4 to 6 minutes. Let cool slightly.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix. Yields 2 cups, enough for 2 small dip dishes.
Serve with Bugles, chips or crackers.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Cream together liver sausage, sour cream and cream cheese; add 1 tablespoon mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add package onion dip and blend well.
Line a bowl with Saran Wrap; fill with dip.
Chill overnight.
Invert bowl on plate.
Remove Saran Wrap and serve with crackers.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and softened cream cheese together.
Add Tang and mandarin oranges.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: crispy chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix Bisquick and pepper in large plastic bag.
Stir uncooked, diced chicken into slightly beaten eggs; remove chicken with slotted spoon and place in bag with baking mix.
Shake bag until chicken is coated; remove chicken from bag.
Heat 1 tablespoons of the oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Stir-fry the 1/2 diagonally cut carrots for 2 minutes.
Add green pepper strips.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Remove from skillet; keep warm. Add remaining oil to skillet; heat until hot.
Stir-fry chicken until golden brown; add the carrots, green pepper and the onion ring slices.
Stir-fry until warm, about 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: marshmallows
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water in large bowl.
Cook sugar and water mixture until it reaches hard ball stage.
Pour mixture over gelatin and beat with electric mixer for 5 to 7 minutes.
While this is beating, beat egg whites very stiff.
Add color to half of mixture; put white in bottom of the pan and colored on top.
Set in fridge for 2 to 4 hours.
Empty pan onto damp cloth; cut into squares and roll in coconut, walnuts or graham cracker crumbs.

title: wine jelly
directions: In the top of double boiler, mix wine and sugar.
Place it over boiling water and stir just until sugar dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in pectin.
Skim the foam, if necessary.
Ladle the jelly through a funnel into hot jars.
Seal. Process for 10 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes 4 half-pints.

title: winter greens puttanesca
directions: Cook pasta to desired texture, (a little firm is best). Cool five minutes. While pasta is cooking, cut peppers in half, roast in oven with skin side up. When browned, skin and chop, put in large bowl. Chop olives, mince garlic, add anchovies (chopped to size). Add washed and cleaned spinach, pour olive oil over this to wilt. Mix all ingredients, feta cheese is added as last ingredient. Top with capers for garnish, optional.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Place pork chops on greased pan.
Sprinkle half of brown sugar on pork chops and half of the cooking sherry on top of that.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Then turn them over and put the rest of the brown sugar and cooking sherry on top and cook for 15 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together and place in baking pan.
Bake in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy homemade rolls
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Spoon into 6-muffin tin.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush 1/3 to 2/3 package of Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and add to crushed Oreos to form crust.
Blend vanilla pudding mix, powdered sugar, milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Add to crust and sprinkle crushed Oreos on top.
Chill.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions. Drain. Crush enough tortilla chips to cover bottom of 13 X 9 baking dish. Spread meat mixture over chips. Pour Ro-tel tomatoes and chiles evenly over meat. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Spread celery soup over cheese. Sprinkle top with grated cheese, crushed tortilla chips and black olives. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with tossed salad, tortilla chips and salsa.

title: double decker knox blox
directions: In a large bowl combine Knox gelatine and jello.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved. Stir in cream quickly and pour into shallow 9 x 9-inch pan and chill in refrigerator. Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with vegetable spray. Pat one can crescent rolls into bottom, removing seams and perforations.
With mixer, mix the rest of ingredients until smooth.
Pour over bottom crust.

title: chicken almond
directions: Skin breasts,
dry
and
salt.	Brown in skillet in the margarine.	Remove to greased baking pan when browned.
To the skillet add almonds, chestnuts, mushrooms and onion flakes and saute.
Add
soup
and
water (or wine); blend.
Pour over the chicken breasts.
Cover
and
bake	at 375° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed, set aside to cool but don't allow to harden.
In a separate bowl, stir remaining ingredients, except whipped cream.
Slowly pour jello into these ingredients, stirring well.
Fold in 1 c whipped cream.
Put in a square 9-inch glass dish and refrigerate.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Roll in ball; put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: ham macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package; drain well. Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
Combine salad dressing and mustard in a large bowl.
Add macaroni, ham, onion, celery, relish, salt and pepper; toss lightly until well blended. Chill.

title: no bake chocolate cookie
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa, margarine and peanut butter.
Boil 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: spoon bread(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine corn meal and cold water.
Add scalded milk and cook over boiling water until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
Combine egg yolks, salt, baking powder and melted shortening or salad oil.
Add to corn meal mixture and mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix butter and dry mixtures together. Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll top of ball into colored sprinkles and remainder of balls into 1/2 and 1/2 cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place sprinkle side up 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: crock-pot special
directions: Take hamburger; make into small balls; brown and drain off grease.
In crock-pot, put layer of hamburger balls, cut up boiled potatoes and 1/2 can peas and carrots.
Add another layer of hamburger balls and potatoes.
Add the rest of the peas and carrots. Dilute tomato soup with 1/4 can water.
Pour over all. Can add minced onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: aunt ruth's potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, bouillon cubes, and onion in a large pot. Cover with water and cook until tender.
Add butter, sour cream, velveeta, and green onions.
Simmer and stir until thick.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk until well blended.
Add crab meat, green onions and cheese.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Even better warmed the next day.

title: glazed apples and franks
directions: In skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Blend in mustard, then the corn syrup.

Slash each frankfurter diagonally in 3 places. Add franks in skillet with apple mixture. Cover and simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until apples are tender and hot. Turn apples and franks once during cooking to glaze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, together and form into ball. Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Melt butter and remove from heat; add milk and sugar, stirring until fondant is easy to work.
Chill.
Drain cherries letting dry for 1 hour.
Take a small amount of fondant pressing in palm until you have a circle large enough to envelope one cherry.
Work it smooth and place on wax paper; chill.
Place a toothpick in each covered cherry.
In a double boiler, melt chips and wax.
Dip cherries once then again and remove toothpick sealing hole with a quick dip into the surface of the chocolate.
Keep cherries in airtight container for a few weeks so fondant will turn to syrup. This recipe came from my first Richland, Washington, neighbor, Jeanette Stanley.

title: salmon surprise
directions: Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup.
Flake salmon and combine with salmon liquid and water.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix together and spoon into 6 greased custard cups.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Unmold onto platter.
Combine 3 or 4 tablespoons milk with remaining soup.
Heat and spoon over salmon.
Garnish with parsley.

title: walnut raisin bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and orange juice and beat well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add 1/3 of flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour mixture and the pineapple with juice.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: peanut butter cup
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marian jeffires' zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini, pineapple and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together. Stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Ice with caramel frosting.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, using a very large bowl.
Add oil, eggs, buttermilk and raisins.
Blend together very well.
Put dough in covered container in refrigerator, and use as needed.
It will keep at least six weeks, the longer, the better.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together, add butter, beat until creamy. Add milk and flour alternately.
Mix well.
Divide batter into halves.
Leave one half plain.
To other half add raisins, cinnamon, cloves, and nuts.
Mix well.
Makes 4 8 inch layers. Makes
2 light layers and 2 dark layers.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Turn out on wire rack to cool.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Let cool.
Add sugar, egg and molasses; mix. Add dry ingredients and mix.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: strawberry and kiwi salad
directions: Arrange kiwi slices in overlapping circles in a shallow dish. Place 1/2 of strawberries, cut side out, around edge of dish to form a border.
Arrange remaining strawberries in a flower-petal pattern in center of plate.
Combine lime juice and fructose and pour over fruit, cover and chill until served.
Makes 4 servings; 74 calories and 0 fat.

title: aunt alice's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients, then mix in buttermilk.
Mix in flour and cut into desired size for biscuits.
Bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spiced carrot sticks
directions: Pare carrots.
Cut into 4-inch strips.
Place in large saucepan with enough salted water to cover.
Cook 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart casserole; cover.
Microwave at High 5 minutes.
Stir well. Microwave uncovered at High until a hard ball stage, 4 to 6 minutes.
Cool 3 to 4 minutes.

title: cheese logs
directions: Mix cheeses, deviled ham and garlic powder with mixer.
Roll in ball and shape into two small logs about 6-inches long. Roll in nuts and chili powder.

title: mac and cheese with tuna and peas
directions: Prepare mac and cheese as directed. Add tuna and peas. Heat through.

title: yeast spoon rolls(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

In a large bowl dissolve yeast in 1 cup of hot water. Mix together the remaining 1 cup water, shortening, sugar, and egg. Add flour 1 cup at a time, mixing after each addition. Spoon into greased muffin pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed catfish
directions: Saute onions and celery in skillet.
Break up cornbread and mix with bread crumbs.
Add mint and salt to bread mix.
Add hot fish stock.
Rub fish down with olive oil and stuff with bread mixture.
Bake in 325° oven until brown.

title: broccoli and chicken roll ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into balls. Mix soup and water in pan.
Drop meat balls in pan.
Cover and cook until rice is done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in a large roaster pan and mix all but pretzels.
Then melt margarine and seasonings together in a saucepan.

After this has been melted and mixed together, pour over first mixture of breakfast cereal and peanuts and stir well. Then place in oven set at 250° and allow it to remain an hour. Add pretzels for the last half hour of heating.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Beat together the powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Melt in double boiler the butter and chocolate.
Combine all ingredients and beat well. Spread on cake and/or use to decorate cake.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry spiced pears(microwave)
directions: Place pears, cut side down, in microwave dish.
Mix cranberry juice and cinnamon.
Spoon over pears.
Microwave 9 to 10 minutes on High or if using canned pears, microwave 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Spoon sauce over pears.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat across the grain into thin strips.
Melt 1/4 cup of butter in large skillet.
Stir in and cook mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Remove the mushrooms.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Note:
Need one plastic sand pail bucket.

title: a.1. barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Ready to use.
Sauce is excellent on beef, chicken, spareribs.
May be stored in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: supper scallop(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Arrange in alternate layers in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, potatoes and your choice of meat.
Melt in saucepan the butter. Remove from heat and blend in flour, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Stir in slowly the milk.
Bring to a boil over direct heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute, then remove from heat. Fold in parsley, cheese and onion.

title: easter egg fondant
directions: Mix milk and cream cheese until blended.
Add confectioners sugar and mix until blended.
Add maple flavor to taste and nuts, coconut or cocoa cherry flavor.
Refrigerate until solid and then dip in chocolate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Eat!

title: potato-beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion (if used).
Stir soup into browned beef and heat well.
Put layer of sliced potatoes in casserole dish, then the meat-soup mixture, then more sliced potatoes.
Pour some milk over top to add moisture.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 1 hour.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots with sugar and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Put in colander or large strainer.
Add celery and raisins.
Mix together.
Stir in mayonnaise and mix well.
Let stand over sink 15 - 20 minutes.
Also good to add a small can of crushed pineapple, drained.
Put in bowl, cover and refrigerate.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and sift into a mixing bowl. Add eggs, oil, applesauce
and brown sugar.
Beat only until well mixed. Add floured raisins with spoon.
You may also add 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: baked catfish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a heavy-duty Ziploc plastic bag. Add fish; seal bag and turn gently to coat.
Place fish on baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake on bottom rack of oven at 400° for 10 minutes on each side.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 5 minutes or until crust is golden and fish flakes easily when tested with fork.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Into greased and floured Bundt pan, place batter.
Bake at 300° for 75 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top of cake after turning out from pan.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix crackers and butter together in bottom of 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine pudding mix, milk and ice cream. Pour over the warm cracker mixture.
Add a layer of whipped topping and sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Chill and serve.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cut pineapple chunks in half and mix with marshmallows; refrigerate overnight.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Beat egg white with water into a froth. In a large zip closure plastic bag, combine sugar, salt and cinnamon. Dip pecans in the egg white. Place coated pecans in the bag containing the sugar mixture and shake, coating them well. Place on a well-greased shallow baking sheet. Bake for 40 minutes or until egg white is dry. Stir every 10 minutes. Cool on waxed paper.

title: corn salad
directions: Chop up tomato, green onions, green pepper and cucumber. Add to drained Shoe Peg corn. Stir in mayonnaise and black pepper. Place in glass bowl and refrigerate until chilled.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place cooked hamburger meat in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese, onion and soup mixed with milk.
Corn niblets or cooked green beans may be added for variety.
Cover with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water seasoned with salt and sugar for 4 minutes.
Drain very well and place in buttered 2-quart flat casserole.
Make a cream sauce with butter (oleo), flour and milk. Pour over the cabbage.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: southern-fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Dip chicken pieces into milk.
Coat with flour.
Dip into egg; coat again with flour.
Fry chicken in 350° deep fat for about 20 to 30 minutes or until browned and tender.
Drain on absorbent paper; serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: split pea or lentil soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and let stand about 30 minutes.
Then boil gently until split peas or lentils are tender.
Add a little broth or water if needed.
Makes about 2 servings, 1 cup each.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain liquid.
Mix ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into hot grease about 350° or medium-low until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: creamy mac-n-cheese
directions: Mix together and bake in a prepared casserole dish at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: hot rice
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
In 2 tablespoons bacon fat, cook onions until soft.
Stir in rice.
Mash tomatoes very well.
Add water, curry powder, salt, red pepper sauce and cayenne.
Mix well.
Add to rice along with green pepper and celery.
Cover and cook on low for 10 minutes. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally, but quickly to keep moisture from escaping.
Serve topped with bacon.

title: farmer's casserole
directions: Place rice in at least a 3-quart casserole.
Add boiling water and salt; set aside.
Brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Mix pimento, soup and soy sauce.
Mix with rice and blend gently.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat and rice are tender. Remove cover the last 15 minutes if a brown surface is desired.

title: egg salad
directions: Add gelatine to cold water; stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir.
Add lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Let cool while grinding up eggs.
Add mixture and mayonnaise to eggs. Pour in dish or mold and chill.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add sugar to beaten eggs. Gradually add flour and undrained pineapple.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken 1 to 2 days ahead.
Save all broth.
Remove all fat from broth and pour into large covered pan.
Bring to boil; add all ingredients and boil 15 minutes on low to medium heat.
Will serve 2 to 3 people.

title: coco wheats sunshine cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add peanut butter and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients into a separate bowl and slowly add the creamy mixture, blend until all ingredients are mixed well.
Add sunflower seeds.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 48 medium cookies.

title: crispy cobbler
directions: Place butter in 8 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Place in warm oven to melt butter.
In a bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk and blend until smooth.
Put in pan over melted butter.
Spread with fruit.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine eggs, onions, broccoli and melted margarine.
Add muffin mix and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 425° until done.
Cut in squares.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Fold in jello.
Let cool. Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans. Pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: spinach strata
directions: In a 2-quart shallow baking dish, arrange 18 Ritz crackers in 3 long rows.
Combine spinach and 2 cups grated cheese; sprinkle half of mixture over crackers.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: new potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets; cool and peel.
Then dice.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Good as leftovers.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Sift together the next 4 ingredients.
Add the sifted items alternately with the other ingredients.

title: boneless chuck roast
directions: Season chuck roast with pepper and brown on both sides in hot shortening.
Add onions and saute.
Add beef broth and can of tomato sauce.
Cover pot and simmer until beef is tender.
Serve with noodles or pasta shells.

title: lazy mans stuffed cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Boil to soft ball stage the Karo, water, sugar, salt, cocoa and peanuts.
Add vanilla and red food coloring.
Stir until loss of gloss.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered wax paper.

title: lee's cream soup(white sauce)
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add milk and salt.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Mix and shape into loaves.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Add fresh blueberries; return to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice; cool.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve over pancakes or ice cream.
May be doubled.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Put pineapple and sugar on stove and bring to boil.
Add Jell-O
and
let
cool.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Freeze. Take
out of freezer about 20 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Use 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Prepare the mashed potatoes.
Beat egg yolks into the potatoes.
Add the cheese, onion, green pepper and celery salt. Whip egg whites into peaks and fold into potatoes.
Spoon into buttered casserole dish, 1/2-quart size.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat yolks well; add milk and sugar.
Beat again.
Add vanilla, salt and fruit.
Pour into 1 gallon (3/4 full) ice cream can.
Crank and eat!

title: beef surprise
directions: Cook hamburger on top of stove.
Add onion, cut in small pieces.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish and bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cover with narrow strips of buttered bread, buttered side up.
Bake until golden brown.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Blend in cocoa; add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Blend in whipping cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Center will be soft but will set upon cooling.) Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in large bowl.
In small bowl, combine egg, milk and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Do not overmix.
Add flour or milk as needed to make batter stiff enough to drop into hot oil.
Drop batter from tablespoon into deep fryer (375°).
Fry until golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle generously with powdered sugar.

title: pacific chowder
directions: Cook bacon; drain, reserving drippings.
Crumble and set aside. Cook onion and green pepper in 2 tbsp of the bacon drippings just till tender.
Add soup, milk, and salt; heat to boiling.
Drain tuna and break in chunks; stir into soup mixture with half the crumbled bacon.
Heat through.
Dash with paprika, if desired. Garnish with remaining bacon.
Serves 4

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add all ingredients and mix. Place in casserole dish; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies to fine crumbs.
Reserve 3/4 cup for topping. Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread softened ice cream over crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
Next, spread chocolate topping over ice cream.
Freeze for 30 minutes. Next, spread Cool Whip over chocolate topping and then sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: new deviled eggs
directions: In a bowl, mix together first seven ingredients until creamy. Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes.
If using frozen corn, simmer first, then drain.

title: green chili enchiladas casserole
directions: In a saucepan, combine soup, milk, olives and chilies together.
Let it cook for about 20 minutes over medium to low flame.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Slice zucchini lengthwise.
Scrape out seeds to make a boat.
Fill with sausage and pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper; spray with Pam.
Mix the first 5 ingredients; pour into the prepared pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix, chopped walnuts and melted margarine on top of the pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Remove from oven. Wait 10 minutes and turn out onto a serving plate.
Remove waxed paper.

title: baked potato soup ii
directions: Wash potatoes. Bake at 400° for one hour. Let cool. Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp. Melt butter in heavy saucepan; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook one minute stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat stirring until thickened and bubbly.

title: apricot compote(aprikoskompott)
directions: Wash apricots.
Soak in water to cover overnight.
Next day, add sugar and cook until apricots are mushy.
Cool and spoon into individual dishes.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream or half and half.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Bake at 400°F for 10-12 min.

title: creamy herb dip
directions: Place sour cream and cottage cheese in food processor or blender.
Process until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: sour cherry cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to first mixture with sweet milk slowly.
Beat well; add nuts and fold in cherries, use juice also.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 layers.

title: chicken casserole with noodles
directions: Cook noodles and cook peas and carrots according to directions on package.
Combine noodles, peas and carrots, chicken, celery and 3/4 of the cheese.
Combine soup, milk and seasonings.
Mix all together, adding 3/4 can of onions.
Mix gently.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: those potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Store overnight in a plastic bag. Peel and shred in a large greased bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top brown.

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef into very small pieces.
Combine with other ingredients.
Form into ball and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans before serving.

title: sugar-free jello pie
directions: Mix well with wire whisk.
Cook in microwave on full power, stirring often, until boils and thickens.
Cool completely.
Add 8 oz. lite Cool Whip (there is a small amount of sugar).
Mix well. Pour into reduced fat graham cracker crust and chill.
Serve with a dollop of Cool Whip on top.

title: carolina gold barbecue
directions: Take a pork roast and rub it with garlic, worcestershire sauce and/or sherry.
Slow cook it in a smoker with hickory chips. Or, if you don't have a smoker, roast it in the oven at 350° until it is falling apart tender.
Remove the roast from the oven and shred it apart in the roasting pan.
Put the roasting pan on
your charcoal or gas grill with some hickory chips and let it soak in the smoke, stirring it occasionally to let the smoke come into contact with as much of the meat as possible.
This won't take more than 30 minutes.
Then take it back to your kitchen and mix in plenty of Carolina Gold Barbecue Sauce.
Get it nice and juicy! If this is too complicated, you can simply boil the pork roast in a big pot with some garlic, onion and a dash of Worcestershire sauce and/or sherry.
Cook it until it's falling apart, then shred it and mix in "The Sauce."

title: alice's mulligan stew
directions: Saute potatoes, onions and meats until done.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Serve hot biscuits and green salad.

title: raspberry bran muffins
directions: Partially thaw frozen raspberries.
In bowl, stir together flour, bran, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center of mixture.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Reserving half of the nuts, mix ingredients well, but don't overmix. Chill. Form into balls and roll in nuts.

title: "gram's" pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix in mixing bowl all wet ingredients together.
Slowly add dry ingredients; mix until well blended.
Grease and flour pans, use 5 x 9-inch of 5 x 7-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or less.

title: san antonio corn
directions: Saute green pepper in butter until just tender.
Add corn and remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, covered; stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: cheesy lasagna
directions: Combine beef, onion and green pepper in large skillet; cook until meat is browned and drain off drippings.
Add fennel seed, garlic powder, pepper, tomato sauce, Italian dressing and parsley flakes; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions, omitting salt; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese; mix well.
Spread about 1/2 cup of meat sauce in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer half each of the noodles, cottage cheese mixture, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: fried green tomato casserole
directions: Layer half of the tomatoes in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add half the crumbs and half the cheese. Top with half the butter in small bits. Layer the other half of the tomatoes with seasoning and cheese. Add remaining crumbs and butter last. Bake covered at 350° for about 30 minutes; uncover and bake another 10 minutes or until brown.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Mix shallot, celery and water.
Blend next four ingredients and stir into vegetables.
Cook, stirring frequently.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir until seafood is thawed.
Add cream.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: In a bowl, combine rice, 1/4 cup egg substitute and half the cheese; mix well.
Pat into bottom and sides of a 9-inch greased pie plate.

title: quick corn casserole
directions: In a large pan stir corn, broth, soup and onions.
Stir in ham and bring to a boil; simmer over medium heat.
Stir to prevent scorching.
Stir in evaporated milk and heat through.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread 1/2 cup coconut on cookie sheet. Toast in oven 5 to 8 minutes or until golden; set aside.
Bake pie shell 8 minutes; cool slightly.
Meanwhile, in medium sized bowl with wire whisk, beat eggs.
Add sweetened condensed milk, water, vanilla, salt and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup untoasted coconut.
Pour mixture into pie shell; sprinkle edge with toasted coconut.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°; bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let pie cool thoroughly before refrigerating.
Refrigerate several hours or until chilled if desired.

title: caracus
directions: Use large skillet and dump all in together.
Cook slowly until thick.
Serve over crackers.
Keep hot in electric skillet or fondue pot.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water.
Stir into gelatin mixture the strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken. Fold into mixture the whipping cream.
Tear angel food cake into chunks and put in bottom of an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish. Pour half of strawberry mixture over.
Makes second layer of chunks.
Top with remaining strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.

title: adult surprise
directions: In individual dessert dishes, drizzle a bit of chocolate syrup on bottom.
Add 1/2 to 1 banana in each one.
Add 1 or more scoops ice cream.
Add a splash of Kahlua over the ice cream.
Drizzle more chocolate syrup.
Top with whipped cream.
Add cherry for color.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute butter and add onion.
Stir in flour; gradually stir in chicken broth until slightly thick.
Add cooked rice, salt, ham, carrots and slivered almonds.
Blend in 1 cup half and half.
Heat through.

title: watermelon refresher
directions: Place half of watermelon cubes in food processor bowl with metal blade or blender container; process until smooth.
Pour into 3-quart, nonmetal container.
Repeat with remaining watermelon. Add juice concentrates and water; stir.
Cover.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Stir before serving.
Serve over ice. Garnish with lemon or orange slices.
Makes 9 (1-cup) servings.

title: caramel nut crisps
directions: Melt caramels with water in a double boiler or in a saucepan over low heat.
Stir occasionally until sauce is smooth.
Pour over combined cereals, coconut and nuts; toss until well coated.
Drop in clusters onto greased baking sheet.
Let stand until firm. Makes 3 1/2 dozen clusters.

title: pizza salad
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on baking sheet.
Press sides out to fill baking dish.
Bake in 300° oven until golden brown.
Let cool; while cooling, mix mayonnaise with the dry Ranch mix.
After rolls have cooled, spread this mixture on rolls.
Chop all remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top of rolls.
Press firmly down with fingers to get vegetables and cheeses down into Ranch mixture.
Cover and put into refrigerator overnight.
Cut into squares before serving.

title: cajun chili
directions: In large skillet, lightly brown sausage over medium-high heat for 7 minutes.
Add chicken, onion and cayenne; cook until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook over medium-high heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix together stuffing mix with 3/4 c. water, mayonnaise, fish and 1/2 c. vegetables. Cover and refrigerate 10 minutes. Heat large nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium heat. Shape 1/3 cupfuls of the stuffing mixture into patties; add to skillet in batches. Cook 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown on both sides, turning over carefully. Makes 6 servings, 2 fish cakes each.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Mix melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs together.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add sugar and softened cream cheese (beaten) to Dream Whip.
Whip.
Place 1/2 cracker mixture in bottom of glass dish.
Add layer of Dream Whip mixture.
Add pie filling as layer.
Continue to layer with crumbs as top layer.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh fried mullet (fish)
directions: Clean and fillet fresh mullet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Put cornmeal in brown paper sack.
Add fresh mullet fillets. Shake vigorously to coat fillets.
Put peanut oil in a heavy iron skillet to a depth of approximately 1-inch.
(Oil should be heated to 450°.)
Fry each fillet until golden brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add 2 cups more confectioners sugar to firm.
Roll in chopped nuts and set in refrigerator.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In a skillet, brown slowly in oil the chicken.
Place in 12
x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
To skillet, add onions and celery; cook until tender.
Add catsup, water, lemon juice, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and mustard.
Season.
Simmer 15 minutes; skim off excess fat.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done, basting 3 or 4 times.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breasts in shallow baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Combine mushroom soup and water; pour over chicken.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake until done.

title: zucchini mexicali
directions: Put zucchini, celery, onions, carrots and peppers in skillet with cooking oil.
Cook 5 minutes stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 4 or 5 minutes longer.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts by hand.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes until light brown.

title: blintze souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a glass "9 x 12-inch" baking dish.
Line with blintzes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, butter and 1/2 cup sugar in bowl. Mix well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes; cool.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and whipped topping in mixer bowl.
Beat well and spread on cooled, baked crust.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine flour, sugar, rind and juice.
Add water slowly and stir constantly over moderate heat.
Add butter.
Season with nutmeg and salt.

title: lemon cooler
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; mix with hands.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed cinnamon biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter or margarine; pour it into a baking pan.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon to the melted margarine.
Stir all ingredients together.
Place biscuits in the pan so that the biscuits are touching each other.
Let them set for a minute, then flip them over.
Bake as directed on biscuit package.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Put soup and water into a pressure cooker and start heating it. Mix hamburger, rice, onion and salt together.
Form into balls about the size of large walnuts.
Drop into hot soup.
Cook at 15 pounds pressure for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: all beef sausage
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 3 rolls.
Place each on a sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil, shiny side out and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Next day, punch holes in bottom of foil with fork (for drainage).
Place wrapped rolls in baking pan (with sides) and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove, drain and rewrap to store.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Slice when ready to serve.
Makes 3 rolls.

title: no bake chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add 1 cup milk and stir until there are no lumps.
Add 2 cups of milk and cook over medium heat until full boil.
Cook one minute only.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(student favorite)
directions: Mix with first mixture and drop by spoonful on wax paper or aluminum foil and let cool.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt, lemon juice and onion in blender or food processor.
Slowly add salad oil until mixture is thick. Remove from blender and mix in poppy seed.
Serve over a bowl of fresh fruit, sectioned grapefruit and avocados.

title: julie's oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crumble all cookies; set aside 1/2 cup for top.
Melt butter and stir into remaining cookies until all are moist.
Flatten out into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together vanilla pudding, cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar.
Spread on top for cookie crust.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cookie crumbs.
Chill.

title: booze cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Mix in dry ingredients. Simmer raisins in water, about 20 minutes.
Use raisins and 1 cup of the water.
Add 1 teaspoon of soda to raisin water.
Do this over bowl as it will foam.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add nuts if you desire.
This will make 18 cupcakes or one 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes for cupcakes, longer for pan cake.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add applesauce and blend.
Add flour, water, soda and cinnamon and mix well.
Add raisins.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° until cake tester comes clean, about 45 minutes.
Good with chocolate frosting.

title: lemon cheese
directions: Beat well eggs.
Add sugar, butter and juice.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Serve on crackers or bread.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together with spoon or large fork until all dry ingredients are blended.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: potato burger pie
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, egg, ketchup, bouillon and pepper. Press into and up the sides of round casserole dish.
Combine potatoes, onion, mushrooms, pimento, green pepper and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Spoon over the meat mixture.
Cover and microwave for 15 to 17 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and cover again until ready to serve.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken in water with bay leaf until tender.
Remove from broth.
Allow broth to cool and harden on top.
Take all fat off once it is solid.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; set aside to rise. Before cooking, mix well again. Drop by teaspoon into hot oil and brown.

title: spam and potato casserole(adapted from ww ii army kitchen)
directions: Alternate
layers of sliced potatoes and cracker crumbs in 2-quart
baking
dish.
Add
milk
and
sprinkle on cheese. Arrange Spam
on
top
and add seasonings.	Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and meat are cooked through.

title: date nut oatmeal bread
directions: Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Make foil tent over pan if bread is browning too much.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Soak bread slices in 1 cup water.
When soaked, crumble into fine pieces.
Combine with chopped onion, chopped parsley, beef, cheese, slightly beaten egg, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly. Shape into loaf pan and dot top with butter.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over loaf; sprinkle with oregano and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: maw maw's sad cake
directions: Mix sugar and biscuit mix.
Stir in eggs, oil and pecans. Spread in buttered 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Serve with coffee.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine and stir well.
Serve 2 teaspoons with 1 cup boiling water.

title: shrimp marinara
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with small amount of marinara sauce.
Add layer of shrimp, then cheese, seasonings and remainder of marinara sauce.*
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in blender.
Cover and run on high for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Pour into crust and chill 2 to 3 hours. Spread with pie filling.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: Heat oil on medium heat in a large skillet or pot, meanwhile beat eggs and milk together in a medium sized bowl and set aside. Pour flour on a dinner plate or in a medium sized bowl, add seasoning salt, and salt & pepper and mix together by lightly shaking bowl or plate.
Rinse chicken and roll in egg mixture and then roll in flour mixture, repeat process once to achieve crispy texture.
Place in oil and deep fry for about ten minutes, a few more if they are large chicken breasts.
You should be able to fry 3 to 4 breasts at a time if your pot is large enough.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute cut up chicken until partially done.
In separate pan, saute onions, peppers and mushrooms until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add spinach, soup, sour cream and paprika.
Combine in casserole with chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° until chicken is done.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Melt butter in pan. Add marshmallows. Stir until melted. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: hot tuna open sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna, onion, celery, milk, seasoned salt and pepper in small bowl.
Mix well.
Cut 5 cheese slices into 1/4-inch cubes.
Toss with tuna mixture.
Split English muffins in half. Divide filling among 6 muffin halves.
Cut each of 3 remaining cheese slices into 4 strips each; crisscross 2 cheese strips on top of each open face sandwich.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken almond bake
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Add celery, onion, nuts and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread 1/2 can chow mein noodles on bottom of baking dish. Pour in chicken mixture.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ring with rubies
directions: Mix first four ingredients and form into a ring mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Add preserves in middle of ring before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: janis' egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar.
Only heat the cup of half and half enough to melt the margarine.
Add this to the other ingredients.
Place in pie crust which has been cooked for 10 or 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for about 1 hour. Take out when center still shakes a little.

title: low-fat chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium sized bowl, combine chicken, tomatoes, chilies, chili powder, onion and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Add about 3/4 cup of salsa; mix well.
Pour remaining salsa in a shallow, wide dish.
Dip a tortilla in salsa and lay on a plate.
Place about 1/3 cup chicken mixture in a strip toward one side of tortilla; roll up and place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Repeat with remaining tortillas and chicken mixture.
Pour remaining salsa over filled enchiladas; sprinkle remaining cheese over all.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 enchiladas.
Two enchiladas constitutes 1 serving.
One serving contains 14 grams of fat.

title: mandarin orange chicken
directions: Rinse with cold water and trim excess fat from chicken; pat dry.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray; add oil.
Place skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken to skillet; cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Drain oranges, reserving juice.
Set oranges aside.
Combine juice and remaining ingredients; stir well and pour over chicken in skillet.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes.
Add reserved Mandarin oranges and simmer an additional 5 minutes.
Serve with rice and pour some of the sauce over the rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts. Shape into balls with hands.
Put on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and cream together. Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Roll in 2 long rolls and wrap in plastic wrap. Chill in icebox overnight. Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cheese danish
directions: Soften cream cheese; beat in sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread one package of rolls in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Spread cheese mixture over rolls, then top with second package of rolls.
Whip egg white until foamy and brush on top.
May sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 350 for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
May sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into meatballs.
Fry meatballs until brown, add water (a little) and cook for 1 hour.
May be placed in casserole after browning and put in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix ingredients.
Trim with fresh strawberries and grapes. Serve with cinnamon crackers.

title: toffee crunch
directions: Mix wafers and melted butter.
Press into bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cream together 1/2 cup butter, sugar, egg yolks, coffee and chocolate.
Add vanilla and beaten egg whites.
Spread over wafers.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle on top.
Freeze. (Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: jello and ice cream dessert
directions: First dissolve gelatin with boiling water in an 8 or 9-inch metal pan (the pan helps gelatin cool faster).
Then remove 1/2 cup.
Pour into a separate bowl.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and thawed strawberries to gelatin in the pan.
Place in freezer until it thickens, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: picnic cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Melt margarine, cocoa and water together.
Mix with flour mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Pour icing on when cake is taken from oven.

title: cran-raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello. Stir in frozen raspberries, then stir in relish slowly. Stir in Sprite.
Pour into a 6 1/2-cup ring mold.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese with 2 cups milk in bowl.
Add instant pudding.
Spread cream cheese-pudding mixture over cooled cake. Top with layer of pineapple.
Whip whipping cream until stiff enough to form peaks.
Spread over pineapple layer.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat
oven
to
Beat
sugars,
margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until creamy
and well blended.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir
in
chips.
Drop
dough
about
2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from pan.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine instant coffee, boiling water and sugar.
Let mixture cool.
Add vodka.
Pour into 1/2 gallon glass jug with 1 vanilla bean.
Close and set aside for 30 days or longer.
HAPPY SOMBRERO! Vanilla bean may be split open if desired.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and set aside.
Melt Crisco in 1-3/4 cup hot water.
Cool.
Stir in eggs and the yeast mixture.
Sift flour on top of liquid mixture.
Make hole in top and put in 1 Tbsp. salt and 1 cup sugar.
Stir and add more flour as necessary.
Knead 5 minutes.
Let rise in bowl for 2 + hours. Shape into rolls and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until brown.
May refrigerate up to 3 days after shaping into rolls.
Allow 6-8 hours for second rising.
Makes excellent cinnamon rolls.

title: punch
directions: Leave ice cream out about 1 to 1 1/2 hours before serving. Mix all 3 ingredients together.
Mmm good!

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Bake brisket in heavy roaster with lid at 450° for 30 minutes. Turn oven to 200° and bake for 5 hours.
No seasonings or water. Remove from roaster.
Let set for 15 minutes and slice diagonally in very thin slices.
Place on serving tray and pour hot barbecue sauce over the meat.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400°F for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and serve.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: easy german oven pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Wipe roast with damp towel and place in pan.
Lay onion rings on top.
Use toothpicks if necessary and roast, uncovered, for 1 hour or until brown.
Lower oven heat to 300°.
Remove roast from oven and add to pan 1 cup beef broth, 1 cup wine, 1/2 cup water, bay leaf, basil, salt and pepper. Sprinkle herbs over meat; lay onion rings in liquid.
Cover the pan with foil.
Poke holes in top of foil.
Return pan to oven and cook 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sour cream and shortening.
Add sugar gradually (very important).
Add eggs alternately with flour and soda which have been sifted together.
Add flavorings.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: creamy tuna twist
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 2 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining items and toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: play dough
directions: Cook and stir vigorously for 3 minutes.
Mixture pulls away from side of pan.
Drop on counter and knead 5 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix soup and sweet milk.
Layer cut up chicken in a baking dish.
Next, add broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over the mixture. Add bread crumbs over the top.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes a big dish.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry mix; stir only until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan or 10-inch skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cake cobbler
directions: Add sugar and spices to fruit.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread over fruit the flour, sugar, baking powder, oil, milk, egg and vanilla.
Put brown sugar and butter on top. Bake in a 350° oven until brown, about 40 minutes.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or bread.

title: strawberry milkshake(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.

title: baked fruit
