directions: Place in a large bowl to mix.
Pour into a large casserole. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is delicious any way it's served but especially good with baked ham.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli until tender; drain and cut into chunks. Place in a buttered, 1 1/2-quart casserole with 1/2 stick of butter.
Stir to melt; then add 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese.
Cut into chunks to aid melting.
Stir well.
Crumble the crackers and add to other 1/2 stick of butter.
Put buttered crumbs on top of broccoli mixture and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: mom's chicken asparagus supreme
directions: Line greased casserole with asparagus and then cover with chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top, then crumbs.
Dot with butter or margarine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, margarine, syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Stir up and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and corn syrup.
Add corn meal, then add beaten eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 glass pan in oven while it heats to 350°. Pour cracker crumbs over melted margarine. Over that, sprinkle chocolate morsels and butterscotch morsels. Sprinkle coconut and milk over morsels. Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool and cut into bars.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl at medium-high speed of an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add sweetened condensed milk, pudding mix and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in 1 quart milk. Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Add remaining 1/2 quart milk.
Freeze mixture according to the manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour. Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: extra special salad
directions: Step 1: Prepare jello by directions, add pineapple and	1/2 c. nuts. Let stand over night in refrigerator.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt
chocolate over steaming kettle.
Add 1/3 of milk. Stir well,
adding
1/3	or so of sugar.
Add another 1/3 milk and 1/3 sugar;
stir.
Add balance of milk and sugar.
Stir 5 minutes. Add
the salt and stir.
Place on slow fire and stir until sugar is	dissolved.
Let boil to soft stage.
Take off the fire.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let stand half hour.
Then place in
cooler place
for 1 hour or so.
Finally place outdoors
to
thoroughly cool.
Add	walnuts
and
work until it begins to set.
Put in buttered pans.

title: caramel - almond topping
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add sugar, flour, milk, cinnamon and almonds.
Boil 1 minute, stirring.
Pour over apple pie filling evenly.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, until topping is golden and bubbly.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in saucepan.
Add boiling water and cook, stirring until clear and thick.
Set aside and let it get cold.
Beat egg whites at high speed until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff but not dry.
Turn mixer to low speed; add vanilla; gradually add cold starch mixture.
Turn mixer to high speed again, beating well.
Spread on pie.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, chopped bananas and milk, then add salt, soda and flour; mix well.
Last add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in layers or long pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until baked.

title: broccoli-rice-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine; add rice, cheese, broccoli and soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off excess fat.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper, and oregano.
Spray 9x13 pan lightly with Pam.
Roll out crescent rolls in bottom of 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle sausage over crescent rolls.
Pour egg mixture over sausage.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: doug's fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add cream.
Bring to boil.
Stir constantly.
Cool over medium to low heat.
Test by dropping in a cup of cold water.
When mixture forms a hard ball, remove from heat, add marshmallow, peanut butter and margarine.
Beat for about 20 minutes or until everything is well melted.
Add pecans. Pour in buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix. Simmer 5 minutes.
Press crescent roll dough into bottom and sides of ungreased pizza pan, pressing edges together to seal.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cover with meat mixture; top with shredded cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Slice into pie wedges.
After your piece is on the plate, add your lettuce, tomatoes and other ingredients as you desire.

title: porcupines
directions: Combine the ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, herb seasoning, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Divide meat mixture into 4 equal parts.
Shape each into a ball.
Press each ball down slightly. Roll each meatball in rice.
Place in a casserole dish.
Combine the tomato sauce with the broth or water.
Pour over the meat balls.
Cover.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until the rice and meat are cooked.

title: italian chicken
directions: Spray pan (9 x 13-inch) with Pam.
Place chicken in pan.
Rub oil all over chicken.
Sprinkle with all spices on both sides. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in bottom of baking dish.
Pour water over apples, then dot with butter and cinnamon.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and corn syrup and bring to a boil. Add in Rice Krispies.
Spread mixture evenly in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together. Spread over top of Krispies (like icing).

title: sausage and rice bake
directions: Brown sausage; pour off drippings.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Simmer until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into baking loaf.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in large mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, combine margarine, cocoa, shortening and water.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Mix with flour and sugar in bowl.
Mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost while warm.

title: sour cream bundt cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add water, oil, eggs and sour cream.
Mix well until moist.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from Bundt pan.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Mix soup, mustard and seasonings together; add salad oil and sugar.
Mix well with carrots and peppers and let stand overnight. Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: italian delight
directions: Fry hamburger and onions.
Add cooked macaroni and corn, then tomatoes.
Add chili powder.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Poke holes in cake and frost with 1 1/2 ??? powdered sugar and 4 tablespoons lemon juice.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss together; add Fritos and dressing just before serving.

title: chicken gumbo, ham or veal
directions: Saute peppers, onion and okra in plenty of chicken fat or butter.
Add meat, tomatoes and water according to whether you expect to make stew or soup.
Simmer gently for at least 2 hours. Waterless cooker is ideal as it conserves fluid.
Serve with rice cooked dry.
Splendid for a supper party as it can be prepared long before rush of last minute duties.
Ham and veal can also be used for gumbo instead of chicken.

title: barbecue's
directions: Simmer and add enough flour to thicken.
Great for picnics.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate squares and shortening.
Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: sugar roll out cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly. Roll thin and cut into shapes. Bake on greased baking sheet at 350° to 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: lemon-basil grilled chicken
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large Ziploc bag.
Mix well. Add chicken and shake to coat well.
Refrigerate overnight, turning once.
Grill or broil 4-inches from heat, turning once (5 to 8 minutes per side).

title: tea room chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, celery, mustard, poppy seeds and salt. Fold in chicken. Cover and chill for 3-4 hours. Top with pecans before serving.

title: barren molasses biscuits
directions: Combine flour, salt, shortening and baking powder to a fine consistency.
Add dissolved baking soda to molasses.
Beat with a spoon until light in color and foamy.
Add molasses mixture to dry ingredients.
Add 1/3 cup milk; stir.
Mix and roll out in desired thickness.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks.
Gradually add milk, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust. Cover with meringue.
Brown in oven at 350°.

title: caribbean pork dish
directions: Cut pork into 3/4-inch pieces and marinate in vinegar, pepper and salt for at least 1/2 hour. Drain and quickly brown in hot oil. Remove and in the same pot, saute onions, peppers, garlic and sausage links. Add saffron and tomato puree. Return the pork to the pot and cover with dry sherry. Cook at least 2 hours. Half hour before serving, add the raisins, olives, almonds and Worcestershire sauce. Serve over rice. This should serve 12 or more. Be sure and use a large pot.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer cooked chicken in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put frozen broccoli over chicken.
Put the 2 cans of soup over the broccoli.
Spread the Cheddar cheese over soup.
Top with onion rings.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Have beef cut 1 or 1 1/2 inches thick.
Wipe with a cloth. Rub seasoned flour (flour mixed with the salt and pepper) into steak or pound in with wooden mallet.
Brown meat in a little fat in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven (brown on all sides).
Add veggies; cover and simmer gently for about 1 1/4 hours, or until meat is tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pam 2 large or 4 small loaf pans.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Spread cranberries on unbaked pie crust; sprinkle with nuts and brown sugar.
Beat egg until thick; gradually add granulated sugar, beating until blended.
Add flour and butter and beat well. Pour over cranberries.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve with Cool Whip on warm pie.
Enjoy!

title: golden oatie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a 9 x 9-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients until well combined.
Press mixture firmly into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until lightly browned and firm.

title: chicken cheese elegant
directions: Place skinless chicken breasts in a large casserole dish.
Do not stack.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Slice onions over chicken. Sprinkle grated cheese over chicken.
Mix together celery and chicken soups.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Can be baked at 250° for 4 hours.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Top each pie with chopped pecans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake for an additional 45 minutes or until center of pie is set.

title: mom's potatoes and smoked sausage
directions: Peel as many potatoes as needed for 1 meal, then cut into cubes.
Let them cook until half done.
Cut up smoked sausage into slices.
Add to potatoes and let cook until done.

title: spinach casserole souffle
directions: Mix sour cream, onion soup and eggs together.
Add spinach and mix thoroughly.
Place in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm in the middle.

title: no-bake peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and honey until well mixed. Stir in peanut butter; mix well. Gently fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Using a microwave, melt chocolate and vegetable oil in a glass measuring cup for 1 1/2 minutes; drizzle over pie. Chill 4 hours. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Make hamburgers, omitting seasonings.
Brown on both sides in skillet.
Meanwhile, combine the ingredients listed.
Drain fat from patties.
Add sauce, cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: stove top crock-pot chicken
directions: When using a whole chicken:
cook until done, remove skin, remove chicken from bones.
Keep broth that chicken made while cooking.
Add to the chicken broth:
sour cream, and soup.
Add the stuffing.
(Do not mix the Stove Top as you usually do.)
Just add to the broth and chicken with the other ingredients.
Mix all together.
Let cook for about an hour in the crock-pot, or to as hot as you desire.
Ready to eat.

title: never fail escalloped corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Excellent.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Defrost veggies.
Cook bacon and crumble.
In a large bowl, combine Cheez Whiz and celery soup and microwave until melted and creamy.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed well with Pam cooking spray.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, stirring every 20 minutes, to prevent sticking.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line
muffin
cups
with baking cups. Spoon flour in measuring
cup;
level
off.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients
except peanut butter cups.
Mix at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Fill muffin cups until top edge	of
each cup is even with the batter. Bake for 18 to
28	minutes
(or until muffins spring back when lightly touched).

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in large pot.
Add water, 1 teaspoon salt, onion, carrot and celery.
Simmer, covered, until tender, 2 to 3 hours. Remove chicken.
Strain and reserve broth.
Strip chicken from bones.
Combine flour, onion salt, celery salt, pepper and remaining 1 teaspoon salt with 1/2 cup of the chicken broth.
Mix until smooth.
Put 3 cups broth in a skillet.
Heat and add flour mixture, using wire whisk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened. Add chicken; blend well.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with pie crust. Cut vents and seal edges.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven layer fiesta dip
directions: On a round pizza pan or large round plate, spread bean dip. Layer mashed avocados over the bean dip; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix, then spread over avocados.
Chop green onions and tomatoes for the fourth and fifth layers.
Spread olives on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese; garnish with sliced avocados.
All you need are chips to dip.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Stir in brown sugar.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on bottom of pan.
Add ice cream.
Sprinkle remainder of mixture on top.
Freeze.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt; drain.
Add soups, sauces and jalapeno pepper which has been chopped fine.
Blend well.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Place a layer of chips on bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of meat mixture over chips.
Add a layer of chips, then remaining meat.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: blake's potato soup
directions: Arrange these ingredients in layers in large, flat pan, approximately 8 x 12-inches:

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve candies in water (reheat if necessary). Add gelatin;
stir to dissolve.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour half into an 8 inch square pan that has been lightly coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cover and set remaining gelatin mixture aside at room temperature.
Meanwhile, combine the cream cheese, mayonnaise, pecans and celery;
spread over chilled gelatin mixture.
Carefully pour remaining gelatin mixture over cream cheese layer.
Chill overnight.

title: texas hash
directions: Add onions, peppers and butter to the drained ground beef. Saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: high desert chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 3 hours.

title: diabetic brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sweetener.
Add eggs and mix well..
Add melted chocolate.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions.
Add all ingredients. Chill.
Save pineapple juice.

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in foil.
Bake in a 400° oven.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Mix soups, milk, onion, chilies and about 2/3 of grated cheese.
Add chicken and a couple of spoons of chicken liquid.
Butter a large casserole.
Put in layers the tortillas and chicken mixture; top with remaining cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours, if desired.
Bring to room temperature.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut slices
of	bread
in 5 sticks.
Heat oven to 200°. Place bread strips in oven for 1 hour.
Heat peanut butter and oil in double
boiler,
stirring
until blended.
Dip 2 bread sticks at a time and roll in powdered sugar and graham crumbs mixture. Place
on
wax
paper
to
dry.
Store
in a can and refrigerate.

title: french vanilla jello
directions: Drain all fruit real good.
Add dried pudding to Cool Whip and mix.
Combine Cool Whip mixture with fruit and mix together. Chill.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch tube pan.
Slice apples.
Mix with 4 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar, then oil. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to beaten mixture in small amounts, alternating with oil and orange juice. Pour 1/4 of batter into pan.
Arrange 1/3 of apples on top. Sprinkle with 1/3 of cinnamon mixture. Repeat layers using 1/4 of batter each time and half of the remaining apples.
Make last layer batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, egg, flour and milk; mix well.
Stir in crab meat, cheese and onion.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream together cream cheese and margarine.
Add confectioners sugar.
Mix and add vanilla and pecans.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: cheese dip
directions: Grind all ingredients and add salad dressing until it is the right consistency.
Add juice from peppers if desired.

title: lemon dill fish
directions: Stir mayonnaise, lemon juice, lemon peel and dill weed until well blended.
Place fish on greased grill or rack of broiler pan. Brush with 1/2 of sauce.
Grill or broil 5 to 8 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue to grill or broil 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raymond's rainbow salad
directions: Mix all these and fold into other mixture.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms set aside. Combine flour, pepper, salt, and eggs, beat with a fork to form a batter. Using a medium skillet, heat oil. Dip mushrooms in batter, fry for about 3-5 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot with gravy.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat all ingredients in a large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or applesauce, if desired.
May be frozen up to 6 months.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Blend soups with milk. Mix with rice, broccoli, mushrooms, chicken, onion and celery. Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle grated cheese on top while hot.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: peanut butter bar classics
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together graham cracker crumbs, confectioners sugar, peanut butter and melted butter.
Press firmly into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips over a double boiler or in the microwave, stirring occasionally. Spread melted chocolate over the crumb crust.
Chill for about 5 minutes, then cut into bars before the chocolate is completely set, then chill until ready to serve.

title: chocolate bit cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well in order given.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
You may add chopped nuts to the mixture if you like.

title: cinnamon apple snack cake
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and egg substitute.
Stir in graham crumbs, apple and walnuts until blended.
Spread batter into greased 8 x 8 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sunshine lemon cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water and cool.
Add oil, salt and extract. Beat in eggs.
Add to cake mix; beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mildred's orange slice cake
directions: Melt butter; mix with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, 3 1/2 cups flour, soda and salt, mixing alternately with first mixture.
Add chopped orange slice candy, dates and nuts. With the reserved 1/2 cup flour, dust fruit and nuts; fold into cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for approximately 2 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until slightly brown.

title: low-fat fruit dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with pineapple, cantaloupe, strawberries, etc.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat soup to boiling point.
Dissolve cream cheese in soup (it helps if cream cheese is room temperature).
Put gelatin in soup-cream cheese mixture; cool slightly.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion, shrimp, salt and pepper. Put into mold and congeal.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and egg.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll out dough and cut into favorite shapes.
Bake in 350° oven.
Bake until light in color.

title: quick sauerbraten
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper; coat meat.
Melt shortening in heavy saucepan; add meat and cook over moderate heat until lightly browned on all sides.
Remove meat from pot and drain off fat.
Add water, vinegar, onion, lemon, bay leaf and spices; mix well.
Return meat to pot; cover and simmer 2 3/4 hours.
Add raisins and cook 1/2 hour until meat is fork-tender. Remove meat to platter.
Use juices and enough water for 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Use with gingersnap crumbs and 2 tablespoons flour to make gravy.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 (9 x 13-inch) cake pan.
Dump pineapple into prepared pan and spread evenly over bottom.
(Do not put all the juice.)
Dump cherry pie filling over the pineapple.
Sprinkle entire box of cake mix (dry) evenly over pie filling.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut on top of this.
Sprinkle walnuts over the top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Do not mix!

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir dry ingredients.
Blend in margarine.
Add beaten egg.
Add raisins.
Gradually add milk until dough is workable and can be rolled into a ball.
Take out of bowl and flatten by hand onto a floured surface to 1-inch thickness.
To shape scones, use cup or juice glass.
Place onto a floured cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Yield:
2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cottage cheese; mix well. Lightly stir in cottage cheese.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and drain. Set aside. Saute onion and pepper in margarine. Add remaining ingredients, except almonds and mix well. Stir in noodles and put into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: french crepes
directions: Combine all ingredients in processor; blend briefly to combine.
Processed batter can be used immediately or stored in refrigerator overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, pineapple, nuts, salt and sugar.
Make three layers of potatoes mixture with marshmallows between each layer. Top with bits of butter and more sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, confectioners sugar and margarine together and knead like bread dough.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin.
Put toothpick in peanut butter balls and dip in chocolate leaving part of the peanut butter showing at the top to look like a buckeye.
Set on wax paper and remove toothpick.
Let dry until chocolate is hard and shiny.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Cover beef with water in large pot.
Cook, covered, for 2 to 3 hours.
Pour off water.
Cover with fresh water.
Bring to boil. Add potatoes, turnips, carrots and onions.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cook until tender.
Arrange meat and vegetables on large serving platter.
Serve with broth or mustard and horseradish.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
Prepare pudding according to package using 5 cups of milk.
In a large punch bowl put 1/3 of cake (crumbled) in bottom.
Top with 1/3 pineapple with juice, 1/3 pudding, 1/3 pie filling and 1/3 whipped topping. Repeat layers 2 more times ending with whipped cream.
Will serve a large group.

title: play dough(this is a real smooth dough.)
directions: Mix together and microwave 4 to 6 minutes to a mashed potato consistency.
Cool on a plate covered with a dampened cloth. Knead.
This can be colored.

title: chinese noodle salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Before serving, add the Chinese noodles.

title: forgotten dessert
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy.
Add sugar slowly; beat to a very stiff meringue. Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Add meringue.
Place in oven; turn off the heat immediately.
Do not open door.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: chicken soup
directions: In a large boiling pot, boil chicken in approximately 1/2 gallon of water.
Debone chicken and put back in broth.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 stacks of crumbled saltines (to thicken soup), 3 chipped hard-boiled eggs and 1/2 gallon milk.
Salt and pepper to taste. Soup is ready after bringing to a boil.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and ginger and stir in soy sauce. Pour mixture over meat and stir.
Cut green peppers and tomatoes into 1/2-inch strips.
Quickly brown beef strips in hot oil and remove from pan.
Reduce heat.
Add green peppers, garlic and water to pan and cook until pepper is tender-crisp, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in meat and tomatoes and heat through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: steamed cabbage au gratin
directions: Cut cabbage into 8 equal quarters, leaving in the core. Lay flat in a large skillet. Pour apple juice over cabbage and add salt and nutmeg. Cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes, covered, until cabbage is crisp-tender. Drain off liquid. Mix together cheese cubes, sour cream and Cheddar cheese. Pour over the top of cabbage wedges. Sprinkle on croutons; cover and place skillet over low heat 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted. Serve hot. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Bring sugar, Jell-O, pineapple and cranberries to a boil. Remove from heat and add fruit, marshmallows and nuts. Pour into oblong dish. Chill until set.

title: creole steak
directions: In large skillet brown steak on both sides in shortening. Remove; saute onions and green pepper until tender in same skillet. Stir in ketchup and remaining ingredients; add meat.
Cover and simmer 50 minutes or until tender, basting occasionally.
Remove steak to cutting board; slice very thinly on diagonal, across the grain.
Skim excess fat from sauce if necessary.
Makes 4 servings (about 1 2/3 cups sauce).

title: chili pie
directions: Combine chili beans, pepper, olives and onions.
Spread over chips.
Spread sour cream over mixture.
Top with cheeses, mushrooms, olives and chips.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 20 minutes.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Mix and press into an 8-inch pan.
Melt the Hershey bar and pour over top.
Let cool for about 2 hours.
Cut in squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Melt magarine with sugar in microwave on High one minute. Beat well, then add eggs.
Beat well again.
Mix buttermilk with soda.
Mix all together with flour, about 2 minutes in electric beater.
Add bananas, pecans or walnuts and vanilla.

title: quick cobbler
directions: *May use self-rising flour if you delete the baking powder

title: apple juice refresher
directions: Chill the juices and mix.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute pepper and mushrooms. Fry bacon.
Remove bacon and brown meat in part of fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook spaghetti in salt water and drain.
With large fork mix together.
Place in oblong dish.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Three hours before cooking, remove from refrigerator.
Bake 45 minutes with cheese on top.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Stir in pumpkin. Stir in milk, chicken bouillon granules, allspice and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring mixture to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour soup into individual soup bowls.
Top each serving with the croutons. Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagna crescent roll-ups
directions: In a large skillet, cook broccoli and onion in oil until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and salt.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce, garlic and sesame seed.
Grill until done; cut into bite-size pieces.
Boil and drain pasta.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a deep saucepan, heat the butter and oil to a medium temperature. Add onions and celery, cook and stir for 5 minutes. Sprinkle on the flour and mix well. Add the broth, water and broccoli, stir and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 15 minutes. In a blender thoroughly puree hot broccoli and return to saucepan. Beat together eggs, milk, pepper and nutmeg. Add to the pan, reheat but do not boil. To serve, garnish with raw broccoli and Paprika. Serves 6.

title: chili soup(48 servings)
directions: This recipe makes 3 gallons of soup.

title: caramel biscuit ring-a-round
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine and water in a 1-quart glass casserole.
Microwave at 75% power for about 2 minutes, or until butter is melted.
Stir in nuts.
Separate biscuits; cut each one into quarters.
Add biscuits to sugar mixture; stir to coat each piece.
Push biscuits and coating away from center of dish and set a custard cup or glass, open end up, in center.
Microwave at 75% power for 5 to 5 1/2 minutes, or until biscuits are no longer doughy.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Twist out custard cup and invert biscuit ring onto serving plate.
Serve warm with forks to pull sections apart.

title: zucchini casserole(serves 12)
directions: Cook zucchini in water in saucepan until tender; drain.
Add soup, carrots, onion and sour cream; mix well.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups stuffing mix.

title: tuna potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Mash; add tuna.
Add mayo until moist.
Add a little mustard to flavor.
Now add paprika, garlic, pepper and salt to flavor.
Great for pita pockets.

title: blueberry-peach pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Put blueberries in bottom of pie.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the dry ingredients on top and add the peaches.
Add the rest of the dry ingredients and dot with butter. Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Put tinfoil around outside edge of crust.
Remove the last 10 minutes.

title: my mother's rump roast
directions: Wash roast with vinegar. Pat dry with paper towel. Pierce roast with fork and sprinkle meat tenderizer all over. Rub flour over roast until covered. Prepare pan or roasting pan with enough foil to cover roast when placed in pan. Place roast on foil in pan and cut onion in large pieces and place over roast. Cover tightly with foil. Keep about a cup of water in bottom of pan entire cooking time. Cook at 375° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: easy orange loaf
directions: Cream the shortening. Continue creaming while adding honey in a fine stream.
Add egg and beat well. Add orange peel.
Sift flour once; measure. Add baking powder, soda and salt and sift together.
Add flour alternately with orange juice, a small amount at a time, to first mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Stir in pecans; blend.
Turn into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes. Turn out of pan and let stand until cool. Wrap in waxed paper or
aluminum foil. Store overnight to blend flavors and for easy slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cinnamon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar together in a bowl; add egg yolk.
Add flour, cinnamon and salt.
Press batter in bottom of generously greased 8 x 14-inch pan.
Beat egg white until foamy; spread on top of batter.
Press nuts on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: molasses bread pudding
directions: Soak raisins in hot water to plump up.
Break bread into small pieces; soak in milk (add more milk if needed).
Add sugar, melted margarine and spices; mix.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add molasses; mix.
Add vanilla.
Drain raisins and add to mixture, stirring well.
Place into greased casserole or deep pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until brown and crusty on top.
It will be solid to touch. Serve warm with lemon or vanilla sauce, ice cream or whipped topping.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix first 4 ingredients. Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture in pan with melted margarine; set aside. Mix baking powder, flour, salt and sugar in another bowl. Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients and milk. Pour into baking pan; sprinkle with rest of brown sugar mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie(easy to make)
directions: Mix all ingredients together over low heat until butter melts. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook in moderate oven about 45 minutes.
Top with meringue.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
In a paper bag, mix flour and seasonings.
Cut up frying chicken.
Place pieces in bag and coat with seasoning mixture.
Place chicken pieces in pan, skin side down, and bake for 1/2 hour.
Turn pieces and bake for 1/2 hour more.

title: hot new potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on in water until tender.
Drain. Fry bacon until crisp, then drain but save grease for later. Crumble bacon.
Sprinkle bacon over potatoes.
Add onions and carrots and stir.
Add cooked pea pods.
In saucepan, mix cider vinegar, mustard and bacon grease.
Cook and stir a few minutes. Pour over potato salad and mix.
Serve hot.

title: casserole
directions: Mix all, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until bubbles in center of dish.
Leave in oven 10 minutes more to set up.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix well; will be thick. Bake in 9 x 12 pan sprayed with Joy. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in a large kettle; add water.
Cover and soak overnight.
Next day, add onion, green pepper, celery, smoked sausage, salt, cayenne pepper and black pepper to the beans in their soaking water.
Bring to boiling over high heat.
Lower heat so that liquid ripples gently.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours. Stir in onion tops and parsley.
Turn to lowest point and cook, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Serve over heated rice.

title: "a" pie (2) by nancy
directions: Stir all ingredients together and put into shells.
Chill. Can be frozen.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix together.
Let set for 1 hour in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and serve.

title: narrow noodles with saffron and veal
directions: Put butter, oil and chopped onion in skillet or saute pan; turn heat to medium-high.
Add veal.
Cook veal, crumbling with a fork and turning until browned all over.
Sprinkle salt and liberal grindings of black pepper, turning meat 2 to 3 times.
Add saffron and cream; reduce heat to medium.
Cook cream down, stirring frequently, until no longer runny.
Toss pasta of your choice with sauce; serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese. Pour into well greased 2 quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle reserved cheese over top.
Continue to bake for about 15 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.

title: apple walnut supreme cake
directions: Set apples and sugar in bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, oil and vanilla; beat 1 minute.
Add dry ingredients with apple mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan 45 to 50 minutes (do not underbake).

title: french potato pie
directions: Shred potatoes in cold water.
Drain and press out water. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and Accent.
Press potatoes over bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in melted margarine until onions are clear.
Pour over potatoes and add cheese.
Beat eggs slightly with milk.
Add mustard, parsley and salt.
Pour into pie pan and sprinkle with paprika.
If you wish, you may add bacon, ham or sausage, but it is not necessary.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before cutting. Reheat 1/2 hour at 250°.

title: apple party mix
directions: In medium bowl, combine cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add raisins and apples; toss to coat with spices.
Add walnuts; toss.
Store in airtight container.

title: praline cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Arrange graham crackers on foil, laying them as close together as possible. Snug foil up closely to edges of crackers.

title: chewy coconut bars
directions: Melt shortening; add sugar and blend.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix.
Add coconut. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (8-inch) square pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut when slightly warm.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix jello with	boiling
water;
let
set
until partly jelled.
Add strawberries and pour on top of mixture in crust. Refrigerate.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Brown meat with onion and pepper.
Slice bread down one side and remove center.
Put bread crumbs in bowl.
Add crumbs, Velveeta and soup to meat mixture.
Do not add water to soup. Stuff loaf with meat mixture.
Put butter on top and heat covered in foil at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumber, onion, carrots, green pepper and whol garlic. Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice, mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours and drain well.
Remove garlic.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture.
Bring to boil.
Fill hot jar 1/2 inch from top.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes (start timing when water returns to boiling). Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: play dough
directions: Cook about 3 minutes on stove.
Knead as soon as dough can be handled.
Store in an airtight container.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4. In a medium bowl combine 3/4 cup granulated sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in the milk, melted butter and vanilla, beat until smooth.
Pour the batter into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In a small bowl combine remaining 1/2 cup of granulated sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa, sprinkle evenly over the batter. Pour hot water over the top.
DO NOT STIR!
Bake for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Let it stand for 15 minutes, spoon into dessert dishes, spooning the sauce from the bottom of the pan over the top.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: spam chicken fry sandwiches
directions: Cut Spam in about 6 or 8 slices.
Roll in flour.
Beat egg and milk.
Dip the floured Spam into egg mixture, then back in the flour.
Be sure and put a thick coating on Spam.
Fry in skillet as you would chicken fry.

title: jam cake
directions: Blend jam, sugar, salad dressing and water.
Sift together flour, salt, cloves, cinnamon, soda, cocoa, vanilla and raisins. Blend everything together and pour in round lined, floured cake pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb conserve
directions: Put together rhubarb pieces, strawberries and sugar into pot. Slowly bring to a boil and simmer until it becomes a jelly-like consistency (thick).
Put conserve into jars, hot and sterilized. Wipe off jars before putting on lids that are hot.
Twist on tight and seal.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and vanilla.
Mix with sweet potatoes. Add milk and cinnamon.
Pour in prepared pie shell and bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Test by dropping a spoonful of mixture into cold water.
If soft balls forms, fudge is done.
Pour into nonstick pan.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise and pimento in food processor container.
Process until blended.
Chill, tightly covered, until serving time.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: annie's cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; form into a ball.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil well.
Add eggs, beating well after each. Add vinegar and food color; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 layers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator.
Easy to make and good.

title: fudge nougats
directions: Combine in saucepan:
sugar, oleo and evaporated milk.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels, flour, crushed graham crackers, chopped walnuts and vanilla.

title: savory turkey scallop
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in skillet; add onion and celery and saute.
Mix with moist stuffing; stir in poultry seasoning.
Spread mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole.
Top with turkey.
In medium saucepan, melt 1/2 cup butter; blend in flour, stirring until smooth.
Stir in broth; heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl; add small amount of hot broth, stirring constantly.
Add egg mixture to hot broth mixture; stir until well combined.
Pour over turkey and dressing.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Last 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle with toasted almonds if desired.
Cut in squares. Serve with creamy mushroom sauce.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add flour and oleo; mix with milk.
Mix all ingredients together and beat with mixer for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pie is done when shakes a little on top.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add coconut and pecans.
Brown lightly.
Set aside and let cool.
Combine the softened cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk using mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Do not beat.
Place half of mixture in each pie shell.
Spread coconut-pecan mixture over each filled crust.
Drizzle caramel topping over each pie. Refrigerate and chill thoroughly.
May be frozen.
Serve right out of refrigerator or freezer.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix everything together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 1 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: islander chicken
directions: Heat the olive oil in a Dutch oven.
Add the chicken, ham, onions and garlic and brown the chicken on all sides.
Add the tomatoes; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat, cover and simmer slowly until the rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Add more water, if necessary.
Remove the chicken.
Heat the rice mixture in the center of a large platter and surround with the chicken. Garnish with pimento, if desired.

title: green bean bake
directions: Combine together milk, soup, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in the beans and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered.
Stir and top with other 1/2 of French fried onions.
Bake 5 minutes more, uncovered. Can add turkey or chicken.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix as directed on box.
Add condensed milk and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix. Repeat procedure, ending with sauce.

title: aunt opal's fudge
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the first 3 ingredients, stirring constantly. Boil for 5 minutes, then pour over remaining ingredients.
Beat until "3" persons are extremely tired.
Pour into buttered pans.
One 9 x 13-inch pan makes very thick fudge, so 2 pans might be best. This is very rich, but so delicious!

title: lumpia
directions: Mix all ingredients and tablespoon into wrappers.
Fold wrappers and seal with a few tablespoons of water and cornstarch mixture.
Fry or deep fry to desired brownness.
Makes approximately 100 pieces.
Uncooked lumpia or uncooked mixture may be frozen.
Lumpia wrappers may be purchased at some grocery stores.

title: quebec maple cake
directions: Beat the shortening and the sugar. Add the flour, salt and baking powder. Then add the liquid ingredients. Whip until smooth. Add the pecans. Pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with Buttercream Frosting.

title: cowboy pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cover beans with water.
Add all ingredients.
Cook with tight lid for at least 8 to 10 hours.
(Do not salt beans while they are cooking; salt seems to keep them from cooking enough.)
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add cake mix and flour. Let rise.
Punch down and let rise again.
Make into rolls and bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a canner or large pot.
Place, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 6 hours.
This need not be checked during cooking.
Can or freeze.
Makes 10 quarts.

title: pizza niblets
directions: Mix mayonnaise and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spread on toast. Place pepperoni slices on each.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Broil in oven for 5 minutes.

title: crock sweet pickles
directions: Heat until dissolved.
Wash medium sized firm cucumbers. Arrange in a clean crock.
Pour mixture over cucumbers.
Let set in a cool place for 2 to 3 weeks.
Be sure that all the pickles are covered with brine.
A stone on a large dinner plate will keep the cucumbers submerged.

title: ken's italian spaghetti
directions: In olive oil, saute bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook beef and drain.
Combine all other ingredients in large pot then add the beef and pepper, onion and garlic mixture.
Cook approximately an hour until done.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and 1 cup of the pecans.
Form in ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill several hours.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt the margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine, pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Garnish with 1 cup chocolate chips with 1 1/2 teaspoons shortening.
Drizzle over bars.
Cut into bars. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: chocolate "black bottom" cupcakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt together.
Add water, oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Beat well.
Fill cupcake papers 1/3 full of batter.
Top each with 1 teaspoon of filling.

title: salmon dip
directions: Remove bones from salmon and crush with fork.
Blend in softened cream cheese and remaining ingredients until smooth. Chill before serving.

title: hot buttered cider(traditional "cure" for a cold, foggy rainy day.)
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mug, pouring scalding milk in lastly and sprinkling nutmeg over top.

title: homemade bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour and blend for 2 to 3 seconds.
Stir into flour and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Grease two 1 pound coffee cans and divide dough into them.
Put lids on and allow to rise until lids pop off.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Allow to cool in can for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on racks.
Bread can be stored in coffee cans.
If a blender is not available, beat by hand or use electric mixer.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Put all the remaining ingredients into crock-pot and simmer.
Add hot dogs and simmer until puffed on ends.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Reserve 2 tablespoons flour to coat walnuts.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk, ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Fold in flour-coated walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes or until done.

title: banana nut bread with orange butter
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside.
In medium bowl, with mixer or wooden spoon, beat sugar, butter and egg until smooth. Add bananas, orange peel and milk, mixing well.
Add flour mixture, beating just until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan; bake 1 hour, or until cake tester comes out clean. Let cool in pan 10 minutes, remove, cool completely on wire rack. Serve thin slices.

title: date torte waffles
directions: Combine biscuit mix, dates, and walnuts; mix and set aside. In separate bowl, add sugar and eggs; beat well. Stir in milk, oil, and vanilla. Gently fold into the biscuit mixture. Bake in preheated waffle baker. Serve with ice cream between 2 hot waffles.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Grease jelly roll pan.
Beat together all bar ingredients. Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
When cool, put frosting on.

title: cheddar cheese pie
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetable stock
directions: Scrub all vegetables; cut off root and stem ends. Do not peel vegetables unless coated with wax. Cut onions into wedges. Cut carrots, potatoes, parsnips and cabbage into 2-inch pieces. In 6-quart Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat. Add vegetables. Cook about 10 minutes or until vegetables are starting to brown, stirring frequently. Stir in the water, salt, desired herb and black pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar and salt together.
Combine well-beaten eggs, melted butter and milk.
Mix with corn mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Stir from the bottom two or three times during the first 30 minutes of baking time.
Double the recipe for a crowd.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time, beating after each one. Add milk and flour alternately to creamed mixture, then add vanilla. Grease and flour 3 eight inch cake pans. Pour 1/3 of batter in one pan. Stir spices, raisins, nuts into remaining batter and pour into other 2 pans. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Julienne and cook green pepper until tender.
In a large bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, garlic, basil, salt and pepper.
Toss in warm pasta and Parmesan.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Add salami, cheese and the tomatoes, quartered.
Garnish with onion rings.
Serves 12.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up and boil the chicken breasts until done in a large Dutch oven.
Add the chicken bouillon and black pepper to taste. Add the dumplings; cook until tender.
You may have to add water as you cook.
Add the oleo and milk; cook no more.
Cover; let stand 30 minutes to an hour before serving.

title: sun dill pickles
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until it boils, then cool.
Pack cucumbers into jars; if too big, cut lengthwise into spears.
Add remaining ingredients to top of cucumbers, then pour liquid over and seal.
Set out into sun for 7 days.

title: shrimp dip
directions: To cook shrimp, bring water to a boil; drop in shrimp.
Turn off water and let stand about 5 minutes.
Shrimp will turn pink; shell and devein.
Mix all ingredients and chill in bowl, covered. Serve with various crackers or chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fresh peach bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: double chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a large bowl, mix on low speed, sugar, oleo, vanilla and eggs until blended.
Increase speed to high and beat until mixture is light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour, sour cream, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Beat until blended, scraping bowl.
Increase speed to medium and beat 1 minute.
With a heavy spoon, fold in zucchini, chocolate chips and walnuts (batter will be thick).
Spread batter evenly in pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes, until a toothpick in center is clean.
Cool cake.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crusty rolls
directions: Mix together milk, sugar, salt and butter.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix both mixtures together, put in 3 cups flour, beat and put in 2 cups flour, forming a stiff dough.
Knead.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Shape into round rolls.
Put on greased sheet, sprinkle top with corn meal after you brush top with water.
Cut top of roll with scissors.
Let rise, then bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: almost snickers
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13 pan. Freeze.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and rinse with water. Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan, parsley flakes and basil. Spread 1 cup of pasta sauce over bottom of a 9 x 13 dish. Stuff each shell with 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese mixture. Place in a single layer over sauce. Spread remaining sauce over shells. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; almost but not until stiff.
Add orange juice, oil and honey, mixing well.
Add all dry ingredients slowly, mixing well.
If mixture becomes dry, add cranberries intermittently.
Mix nuts in by hand and pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then cool on wire rack.
Wrap and refrigerate.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: Wash and cap strawberries; drain well.
Place a single layer strawberries in a shallow pan; freeze.
Combine buttermilk and remaining ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 1/2 cups (59 calories per 1/2-cup serving).
Contains 2.3 g protein, 0.4 g fat, 12.7 g carbohydrate, 1 mg cholesterol, 57 mg sodium and 72 mg calcium.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Sift over fruit and nuts in large bowl.
In a separate bowl, beat the 4 eggs and add vanilla.
Pour over ingredients in a loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 250° (slow oven). May take longer.
(Grease loaf pan with Crisco, line with wax paper and grease paper also.)

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and water.
Heat to almost boiling. Put a layer of potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add layer of onions and pour 1/2 of soup mixture over this.
Put another layer of potatoes on top of this and add salt, pepper, rest of the onions and chicken soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves about 6.

title: spanish coffee
directions: Dip rim of glass in lime juice.
Dip in sugar.
Combine the ingredients.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Sift flour with salt and soda. Cream butter, peanut butter, brown sugar and 1/2 cup granulated sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Add flour mixture and beat well. Put remaining sugar on waxed paper. Shape dough in balls. Roll in sugar. Bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven; press chocolate pieces in centers. Bake 2 to 4 minutes longer.

title: baked bean reunion
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground chuck and drain.
Combine rest of ingredients with cooked ground chuck and bacon on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli with lemon sauce
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Whisk together 1/2 cup water, lemon juice and Dijon mustard.
Put in saucepan and heat. Add cornstarch mixture and continue heating until mixture thickens.
Add lemon juice if needed to make desired consistency. Blanch broccoli in boiling water or steam until done.
Toss with lemon sauce.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer with coconut and nuts.
Mix cake by directions on cake box and pour over nuts and coconut.

title: artichoke pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain well. Rinse with cold water and drain again.
Place in a large bowl.

title: chicken salad pies
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pecans, onion and chopped eggs.
Toss gently.
Stir in lemon juice and salt.
Cover and chill.
When ready to serve, stir in mayonnaise.
Spoon evenly into cheese pastry shells.
Garnish with egg quarters and watercress.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix
all ingredients and store in jar.
Use 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread broccoli in dish.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, cream of mushroom, onion, salt and pepper and pour over broccoli, then spread cheese and then bread crumbs and oleo.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in 1 stick butter until light, but not brown.
Add soup, Worcestershire sauce, rice and Cheez Whiz.
Mix until cheese melts.
Add broccoli (well drained).
Bake in casserole at 325° for 20 minutes.
Bake, covered.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour creaM, cucumber, onion, egg whites and dill; chill.
To serve; top greens with tuna.
Garnish with egg and tomato wedges.

title: lazy pierogi
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and fry.
Cut mushrooms into slices and saute in butter.
Drain sauerkraut.
Combine bacon, onions, mushrooms and sauerkraut with undiluted mushroom soup. Cook pasta; do not overcook.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole; mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and salt in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rolled oats, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: aunt hazel's swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix with wet hands and shape into small balls.
Heat 3 tablespoons bacon fat and brown meat.
Remove meat and add flour. Brown flour in remaining fat.
Stir in consomme, Sauterne and milk. Cook until thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Return meat to gravy.
Add chopped parsley and simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 6. Serve over pasta or rice.

title: party potato chips
directions: Spread potato chips on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cheese and herbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into meatballs, roll in flour and brown in hot oil until brown.
Put in hot tomato sauce and simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and raisins; mix well.
Press dough onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pound cutlets between sheets of plastic wrap to tenderize; put cutlets into skillet containing melted butter, salt and pepper and turn before cutlet browns.
Cover skillet tightly; cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
While chicken is cooking, prepare rice. Melt 3 tablespoons butter; simmer with 2 tablespoons minced onion. Ross rice into butter/onion mixture to coat rice.
Boil 3 cups water and bouillon; pour over rice.
Add bay leaf and cover. Bring to boil again and immediately place, covered, into 350° oven for 17 minutes.
Remove cooked cutlets to a warm plate.
Save drippings from chicken and boil away any excess liquid in frying pan, reducing liquid to chicken drippings without scorching.
Add sweet vermouth; stir for 30 seconds.
Add cream and stir constantly until it boils; shut off immediately.
Place cooked rice on platter; arrange chicken on top and pour same amount of cream sauce over chicken/rice.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter with dry milk, then add raisins or chocolate chips.
Roll into balls and roll in crushed cereal.
Chill and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and set aside.
Cook the onion, bell pepper and celery in oil until soft. Add water, gravy, mushrooms, tomatoes, cheese and chicken.
Spray casserole with Pam. Layer sauce mixture and spaghetti. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar.
Roll into small balls.
Put in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in with a toothpick. Cover only 3/4 of the ball.

title: country style pork roast
directions: Mix together the above listed dry ingredients and rub into the pork roast. Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: orange-glazed beets
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine honey, orange peel, orange and lemon juice and salt.
Add beets.
Mix very gently.
Refrigerate several hous to overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain and serve as a relish.

title: layered chalupa dip
directions: Combine beans and taco sauce in a small saucepan.
Mix well. Heat thoroughly.
Spread in bottom of a shallow serving dish. Peel, seed and mash avocados.
Blend in lime juice, oil and garlic salt. Spread over bean layer.
Layer next 6 ingredients over avocado layer.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes about 12 to 16 appetizer servings.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Cake:
Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes. Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix Spry, sugars, vanilla, and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt, and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add oats and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Bake 12-15 minutes on greased sheet at 350°.
Cool 2 minutes before removing.

title: broccoli jennifer
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Butter a 1-quart casserole.
Beat egg in medium bowl and add soup, mayonnaise, cheese and onion. Put broccoli into casserole and pour mixture over top.
Stir until blended and cover top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 oz. almond bark in a large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts. Pour into greased 12 inch pizza pan. Top with cherries, sprinkle with coconut. Melt remaining 2 ounces almond bark with oil over low heat, stirring until smooth. Drizzle over coconut. Chill until firm. Store at room temperature.

title: eight bean soup
directions: Rinse and soak beans overnight in water to cover.
Drain. Combine drained beans with all ingredients (except tomatoes and vinegar).
Add broth packets if desired.
Cook until all beans are tender.
Use cover.
When beans are tender, add tomatoes and more water if needed for desired consistency.
Heat thoroughly an additional 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage in medium skillet until browned; drain and set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles; place triangles with elongated points toward center in a greased 12-inch pizza pan. Press bottom and sides to form a crust; seal perforation.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on lower oven rack.
Crust will be puffy when removed from oven.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients. Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Garnish with pepper slices if desired.

title: pittsburg potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in water with cover on for 5 minutes.
Add pimento and onion and cook until tender.
Drain and put in buttered dish.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and stir.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat slowly until cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: bridget's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook bow tie pasta with dash of salt and 1 tsp olive oil in water until almost done. Drain and rinse.
Make layers of pasta, cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses until
they are gone.
Bake at 350 until top is brown (approx. 20 minutes).

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix together; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Cut wieners into bite size pieces.
Place rest of ingredients into crock-pot and mix well.
Put wieners in with the sauce and simmer on high 2 hours or low 3 to 4 hours.
Serve hot.
Sauce can be frozen and used again with more wieners.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pat into loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter; add broth.
Bring to boil; add shells. Cook 5 minutes.
Add frozen broccoli and cook 4 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and milk.
Heat just until warm.
Add cheese.

title: o.g.m.  chicken(onion, garlic, mushroom)
directions: Place chicken thighs in deep baking dish or microwave dish. Pour the Worcestershire sauce over chicken generously.
Slice onion thin and place on top of chicken.
Slice mushrooms thinly and place on top of chicken too.
Sprinkle garlic powder over everything.
Cover and put in microwave for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Yes, on High.

title: homemade ice cream(no eggs)
directions: Mix well and freeze in ice cream freezer!

title: corn bread
directions: Scald cream with butter.
Mix Bisquick mix, sugar, corn meal and baking soda.
Add cream, butter and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to stand for several minutes before cutting.

title: slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour in lemonade and orange juice and mix well.
Pour in gin or vodka and mix well.
Freeze in cake pans for 24 hours.
Mix two spoonfuls frozen mixture with cold 7-Up or Squirt and ice.
Drink.

title: roasted red pepper and eggplant
directions: About 3 1/2 hours before serving or early in the day, preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
Line broiling pan with foil. Prick red peppers in several places to prevent them from bursting when broiling.
Place peppers in broiling pan.
Place broiling pan in oven about 6-inches from source of heat; broil peppers until charred and blistered on all sides, about 20 minutes, turning peppers occasionally.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken over rice.
Mix soup with water and pour over top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, salad dressing, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Lay one of the crusts in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix vegetables, soup and chicken.
Pour over crust in casserole.
Top with second crust.
Pinch edges and brush with butter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hobo cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: catalina chicken
directions: Place breasts in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix 3 ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Can use chicken breast with bone and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: glogg
directions: Step 1:
The foundation of the glogg can be made several days ahead.
Place the whole cloves, whole cardamom seed, coarsely shredded almonds, raisins, orange peel and cinnamon in a kettle with enough wine to cover (any kind); bring to a boil.
Cool.
Pour this into a jar; cover and store until your party.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt that has been sifted.
Blend well.
Add apples and nuts a little at a time.
Mix well.
Pour in a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix; add nuts.
Shape into balls; put on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Put chocolate pieces and 2 T water in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling water). Stir until melted.

title: heavenly eggs
directions: For 6 eggs:
Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with desired combination of seasonings.
Refill whites. For color, put a little paprika on top.

title: chicken n' cranberries
directions: Pour the bottle of French dressing into a bowl and add the whole cranberries and package of soup mix.

Mix all together and place the chicken breasts in baking dish covering with the sauce. Let stand overnight in refrigerator (okay to let stand for 3 to 4 hours prior to baking, but is better when kept overnight).
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesy tortilla corn
directions: Cook and stir onions and red pepper in 2 tablespoons of margarine in a large skillet over medium-high heat until tender. Reduce heat to low.
Stir in corn and Velveeta.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes until cheese is melted and mixture is thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons of margarine in separate pan.
Stir in tortilla chips and seasoning.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Spoon corn mixture into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with tortilla mixture.
Garnish with additional cilantro and red pepper, if desired.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix well and press into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Chill.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine
first three ingredients and let jell a little. Prepare
Dream
Whip
as directed.	Add pineapple and oranges. Fold together and chill.

title: kentucky fried chicken slaw
directions: Combine
cabbage,
carrot
and onion in food processor. Combine remaining ingredients well.
Pour over cabbage mixture well.
Refrigerate	in Tupperware container overnight.
Serves 12 people.

title: great english pea salad
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: In medium saucepot of boiling water, cook pasta to desired doneness; drain and cool. (Rinse with cold water to cool quickly.) In a large bowl, combine cooled pasta, mixed vegetables and onion. Mix well. In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, sugar, dill weed, salt and pepper. Blend well. Pour mayonnaise mixture over pasta-vegetable mixture. Toss lightly. Chill before serving.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like pie crust and put in bottom of an 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes.

title: whipped topping 2
directions: Combine milk, water, lemon juice, vanilla and sweetener in small bowl of mixer.
Beat for 1 minute; add dissolved gelatin and continue to beat until the mixture is thick and stands in soft peaks.

title: surprise chili
directions: Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan.
Brown meat, onions and garlic. Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Simmer partially covered for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy salad
directions: Dissolve candies in 1/2 cup of boiling water.
Dissolve gelatin in other half of the water.
Combine gelatin and candy mixtures and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold applesauce into mixture.
Chill until set.

title: lottie's porcupines
directions: Form first 5 ingredients into 8 balls.
Place in lightly greased casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling point.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°, covered.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and combine all ingredients, except onion rings.
Turn into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add onion rings on top and bake, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in hot oil.
Remove and let drain.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1 can of water and heat.
Place potatoes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with celery, onion and bell pepper and place pork chops on top.
Sprinkle with rest of onion, pepper and celery.
Pour on soup.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: the best cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello by dissolving in 2 cups hot water and 1 cup of reserved pineapple juice (if there is not enough, add water to equal 1 cup).
Mix in all other ingredients (orange, cranberries and sugar).
Put into mold.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat broth and bouillon to boiling point, but do not boil. Fry onions in butter until tender; not brown.
Add to beef broth and bouillon.
Add to broth mixture.
Refrigerate until chilled. Take out of refrigerator after chilled or before ready to serve and bring to a boil; heat thoroughly.
Spoon into individual bowls or cups that will stand up under broiler heat.
Put 1 slice dried out bread, with crusts removed, on top of soup; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Put under broiler until golden brown. Serve immediately.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil in a large stockpot; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Remove chicken, reserving broth. Skin, bone and cut into pieces; set aside.

title: tea time sandwich
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill. Makes 10 sandwiches.
Cut to desired shapes.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Peel and slice apples in pie crust.
Make custard with eggs, milk and sugar.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° until done. Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions, Accent and part of meat (leave enough meat to roll ball in).
Form into a ball.
Roll in remaining meat.
Chill and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: tomato conserve
directions: Wash and clean tomatoes; cut into pieces.
Put oranges and lemons through food chopper.
Place all ingredients in large kettle and cook until thick.
Place in pint jars and seal with tops and rings while still hot.

title: bacon-broccoli salad
directions: Cut fresh broccoli into bite-size pieces; chop 1 medium onion fine. Fry bacon until crisp and crumble when cool.
Mix broccoli, onion and bacon together in a large bowl; set aside. Combine Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar. Pour over broccoli mixture. Stir and refrigerate. Best if allowed to set overnight.

title: vegetable strata supreme
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
Arrange frozen vegetables in bottom of prepared dish; sprinkle with bread cubes and ham.

title: stuffed peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a baking dish.
Peel one peach. Cut flesh in pieces.
Cut remaining peaches in half.
Remove pits and scoop out a bit of the pulp from each half.
Combine pulp with cut up peach and mash well with a fork.
Add butter and crushed macaroons, egg yolk, cream and cognac; mix well.
Fill each peach half with mixture, mounding it slightly.
Arrange in baking dish and bake 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Reduce to simmer and add margarine and vanilla. Serve hot.
Yields 2 cups.

title: ramen salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Mix together last 3 ingredients along with seasoning package from Ramen noodles. Mix together both combinations. Chill.

title: frosted apricot jewels
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter and cheese, pastry blended until coarse meal.
Add coconut and apricot preserves.
Mix well.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonful 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (18 minutes) until lightly brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Spread frosting and top with pecan halves.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling and pineapple.
Put pats of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy pecan clusters
directions: Place marshmallow creme and Kisses in a large bowl; set aside. Combine milk, sugar and butter in a saucepan. Boil mixture to a high point, let boil 8 minutes (or until a soft-ball stage). Pour over marshmallow and Kisses; blend well. Add pecans and mix. Drop by the teaspoon on waxed paper. Makes 12 dozen clusters.

title: chili
directions: Chop onion and pepper.
In large electric frypan or skillet, fry onion and pepper in a small amount of oil.
Add stewed tomatoes and vegeburger, stirring constantly to brown vegeburger. Add tomato paste and beans.
Cook until well heated.
