Season with garlic salt and onion powder to taste.
Serve on top of Fritos with lettuce, cheese, tomato and sour cream and don't forget the hot sauce.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7
ingredients together well and place in shallow casserole and top with a mixture of brown sugar, flour, pecans and melted oleo.
Mix and crumble over top of potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on round pizza pan; sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake until golden brown.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Spread over cooled cookie.
Then dip the thinly sliced bananas in lemon juice and place on Cool Whip mixture.
Add peaches and grapes.
Top with 1 can of drained crushed pineapple.
You can use any combination of fruit, such as strawberries, kiwi and mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop vegetables fine.
Bring all ingredients to a boil. Continue boiling for 1 1/2 hours.
Add 1 cup vinegar before removing from stove.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: scallop soup of the tribes from n.e. coast
directions: Place scallops, water, scallions and watercress in a large saucepan and simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: leeks and eggs au gratin
directions: Place the eggs in a saucepan; cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 7 minutes (yes, time them!). Remove from heat; immerse in cold water.
Wash the leeks; cut them into 1/2-inch slices.
Heat 1 ounce butter in a medium size saucepan.
Add the leeks; allow to steam with the lid on for 5 to 6 minutes, or until just tender.
Melt the remaining 2 ounces butter in a small saucepan.
Add the flour and milk all at once. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until the sauce has thickened.
Add 2 ounces grated cheese; continue stirring until the cheese has melted.
Season with a little salt and pepper.

title: red slaw
directions: Young bucks such as Thumper, need only a couple hours of soaking in salt water to draw off blood, but old Bugs should be soaked up to 18 hours to draw out the orneriness! To clean wabbit, cut stomach from rear to ribs, hold by the front legs and snap quickly. The insides will just fly out, usually all over your partner's gear if not careful. Cut rabbit into serving pieces. Put on rack in baking pan. Bake 1 1/4 hours in hot oven. Brush every 15 minutes with barbecue sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° about 1 hour.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Mix all together, adding frosting last. Bake in a tube pan or 3 (9-inch) pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Brown the diced bacon. Remove from grease and place into a pan containing the pork and beans. Add the brown sugar, yellow mustard B.B.Q. sauce, and dried onions. Mix well. Add 3 tbsp. bacon grease. Taste. You should be able to lightly taste the bacon, if not, add 1 more tbsp.

Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often. When it begins to boil, cover and lower the heat. Let simmer at least 1 hour at lower temperature. Stir often. Turn off heat, remove lid and let stand for 10 minutes. Eat and enjoy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing; shape into ball by rolling in bag.
Then roll in pecans.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: chops and spuds oven bake
directions: Salt
and
pepper chops.
Coat with flour.
Rub in dash of curry
powder
on
each
side.
Heat
oil in heavy skillet. Brown chops
on each side.
Place in oblong dish.
Cook onions in skillet until soft.
Add mushroom soup and 2 cans of water. Add sliced mushrooms; bring up heat until the mixture bubbles. Place potatoes
in dish between chops.
Pour mushroom mixture over chops and potatoes.
Place in oven preheated to 350° and bake 1	hour. Add
Velveeta cheese over top of chops and potatoes.
Bake until
cheese melts.
Serve with hot biscuits and butter.

title: italian chicken casserole
directions: Combine rice, 1/2 can onion rings and 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour bouillon mixture over rice.
Arrange chicken on top and pour on Italian dressing.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven, place vegetables around chicken, covering rice.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 1 to 3 minutes.

title: just plain meat loaf - that's not so plain
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Add milk.
Let it sit up and snap, crackle and pop for 5 minutes.
Break up ground round and gradually add.
Mix the ground beef with the mixture.
Mix in chopped bell pepper, onion and celery.
Shape meat mixture in shape of loaf or football.
With the side of your hand, make a deep groove in the top of loaf. Tuck the cheese into the groove and squeeze the sides of the loaf to close groove.
The cheese will melt inside the loaf.
Poke holes along top and side of loaf with your index finger.
Make the holes about 1 to 2 inches deep.
Fill the holes and the top of groove with catsup or spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chipmunk cake
directions: *Do not add liquid to the mix as the pudding is the moistening ingredient.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Put in large bowl.
Add peas, chopped onion, tomato and chopped eggs.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Combine all with tuna.
Refrigerate for about an hour.

title: no stir peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish (use dish you plan to cook in).
In another dish, stir flour, sugar and milk.
Pour this mixture in dish over margarine.
Don't stir.
Pour fruit on top. Don't stir.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese and onion.
Pat 2 packages frozen broccoli in a flat casserole dish.
Cook broccoli 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour ingredients on top and smooth; cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Make a well in the center; add eggs and oil, stirring only until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in berries and nuts.
Spoon batter into 2 lightly greased 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in middle.

title: herb roasted lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut small slits in the lamb and insert garlic slivers with tip of knife.
Combine remaining ingredients and rub thoroughly over and into meat.
Roast on a rack in a roasting pan, uncovered.
Cook 18 minutes per pound for medium. Let stand 20 minutes, then carve.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Smash shrimp with fork.
Cut celery and onion in very small pieces and add to cream cheese.
Mix with fork, then add lemon juice.
Form in ball.

title: gazpacho(spanish cold soup)
directions: Chop vegetables coarsely.
Put all ingredients in a blender and puree 5 seconds.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
(Improves in sitting.)
Serve with diced tomatoes, cucumbers, green pepper, scallions and croutons.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground sirloin and onion in soup pot.
Add all remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for a couple of hours. Stir frequently.
Serve with a variety of toppings: chopped avocado, crushed taco chips, chopped green onion, sour cream, grated cheese, chopped fresh cilantro or chopped black olives

title: grandmomma's punch
directions: Chill juices; mix together.
When ready to serve, add chilled ginger ale and sherbet.
Serve.
Easy to double or triple.
Makes 20 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, sugar and soda.
Then add milk, butter, cinnamon, oatmeal, raisins and eggs.
Drop from a spoon and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn casserolenederland, texas
directions: Saute onion, pepper and oleo.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and mix well.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 325° for 45-55 minutes.
10 minutes before done, top with grated cheese and finish baking.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil.

title: quickie pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread tomato sauce on bagels.
Sprinkle cheese and oregano on top. Bake 20 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Slice in thirds and serve. Makes 24 appetizers.

title: baked cream cheese appetizer
directions: Variation:
Substitute combined 1/2 teaspoon dried rosemary leaves (crushed) and 1/2 teaspoon paprika for dill seed.

title: ricotta cake italiana
directions: Follow directions for cake mix and prepare.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: guess and by gosh cake
directions: Simmer raisins until tender.
Drain off liquid into cup, draining enough liquid to make 1 cup (cool).
Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix wet ingredients and beat until fluffy. Gradually stir in dry mixture and raisin juice.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: "cheese cake - soft"
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and lemon extract and put in crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread lemon pie filling on top. Double for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat Wesson oil and sugar together. Beat in eggs. Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately with applesauce. Beat in vanilla. Stir in raisins, dates, walnuts and pecans. Put in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs with mixer on high until smooth.
Pour over cake mix mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat shortening with sugar.
Beat in well beaten eggs.
Stir in soda.
Add crushed bananas.
Mix flour and salt.
Add to mixture.
Pour in loaf pan (greased).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: speedy baked beans
directions: Note:
Weight of beans may be from 57 to 70 ounces total.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Make each small package of jello separately per package instructions, but use only 1/2 cup water instead of 2 cups.
When jello is firm, cut into small cubes.
Place in refrigerator for now.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip, then spoon into graham crust.
Place in refrigerator for several hours to set.

title: quick corn and zucchini saute
directions: In large skillet, saute peppers and zucchini in oil until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Add corn, garlic powder, salt and Italian seasoning.
Cook until heated through.

title: penny's scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash and pare potatoes.
Slice thin.
Place 1/2 potatoes in baking dish, greased.
Sprinkle with onion, meat, flour and bits of butter.
Repeat process.
Add milk so it can be seen between top slices.
Cover and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more or until tender.
Then top with a little shake of paprika to color.
Also could add shredded cheese last 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Pour into 3 small, well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: o'mama's "medicinal" hot toddy
directions: At the onset of cold or flu, put patient in bed under lots of covers.
Put lemon juice in tall mug.
Add honey and whiskey.
Fill mug with boiling water.
Stir well and have patient drink while very hot!

title: pickle relish
directions: Grind in food chopper with medium knife.
Mix 1/2 cup salt through this and let stand 2 hours.
Drain and add 3 pints diluted vinegar, 6 cups sugar, 1 tablespoon celery seed and 1 teaspoon mustard seed.
No cooking.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Seal at once.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Brown sausage and drain well. Saut celery and onion in margarine until tender. Mix together rice, sausage, celery, onion and mushrooms. Pour into prepared casserole dish. Top with almonds. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: quick and easy caesar salad
directions: In a food processor, combine ingredients.
Process the ingredients until fairly smooth.
Pour over large croutons and soak for 10 minutes.
In a large salad, pour dressing/croutons over romaine lettuce.
Toss and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: almond cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Grease cookie sheet. In small bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, almond extract, almonds and cherries. Mix well. Unroll crescent rolls into 2 long rectangles. Overlap enough to press edges together. Spoon cream cheese mixture down middle of pastry. On each long side of pastry, make cuts 1-inch apart up to filling. Fold over strips on each side to make a braid look. Seal each end. Brush top with egg. Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and drizzle glaze over coffee cake. Garnish with cherries.

title: easy lemon pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil and blend with mixer for 2 minutes. Pour cake batter into Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. In small bowl, spoon out 1/2 container Betty Crocker lemon frosting and heat in microwave just until warm on Low power. Drizzle over cooled cake for lemon glaze.

title: strawberry tall cake
directions: Bake cake according to package instructions for 2 layer cakes; cool completely.
Slice the layers in half and place in the freezer.
Slice strawberries and mix with the strawberry glaze. Reserve 3 tablespoons of the mixture for the top of the cake.

title: pineapple-cream cheese
directions: Mix and serve on breads, crackers, etc.

title: swiss mocha mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. If desired, add a vanilla bean to the mixture for flavor. For 1 cup of beverage, use 3 tablespoons to 6 ounces boiling water.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on each side.
Pour can of tomato sauce over pork chops and top with a slice of pepper.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Top with a slice of Mozzarella cheese and heat until the cheese melts.

title: sweet and sour stir-fry chicken
directions: Assemble all ingredients. Preheat large skillet or wok over high heat for 10 seconds.
Add oil to skillet and heat for 15 to 20 seconds.
Carefully add chicken strips and stir-fry until chicken is cooked, about 5 or 6 minutes.
Add vegetables and pineapple, stir-frying 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in sweet and sour sauce.
Continue stirring until sauce covers all ingredients and is thoroughly heated. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add seasonings.
Blend in soup and stir until smooth.
Gradually add evaporated milk, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
In casserole dish, mix spaghetti, mushrooms, pimento and chicken.
Pour in sauce and mix.
Top with Cheddar and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Can make ahead and keep in refrigerator.
Take out 30 minutes before dinner and bake as directed.

title: ricotta and arugula
directions: Cook pasta as label directs until al dente, cooking garlic with pasta.
In serving bowl, mix cheeses, pepper flakes and the salt. Place arugula in large container.
Add 1/2 cup pasta water to bowl with cheeses; mix.
Drain pasta and garlic in colander with arugula.
Add to cheese mixture; toss.
Sprinkle with pine nuts. Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad with nuts(german style)
directions: Scoop out melon with melon baller.
Cut peel from oranges; remove white membrane and slice crosswise.
Cut grapes in half; remove seeds.
Line glass bowl with lettuce leaves.
Arrange melon, orange, grapes and walnuts in layers on top lettuce.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice as thin as possible. Chop onions and celery; combine with cucumbers and salt. Let stand for 3 hours. Drain well. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in large pot and bring to boil. Put in cucumbers and heat thoroughly. DO NOT BOIL! Pack while hot into jars and seal.

title: o'charlie's caramel pie
directions: In a large saucepan, bring approximately 8 cups of water to boil.
Put unopened can of Eagle Brand milk in water to boil 5 hours.
Add water when needed to fully submerge can.
Remove can from water and cool.
Open can carefully and spoon contents into pie shell.
Spread evenly and top with Cool Whip.
Shave chocolate bar on top.
Chill and serve.

title: tomato juice appetizer
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients (cake mix, margarine and egg).
Spread into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.

title: pralines
directions: Combine in a large pot and cook over medium heat until it forms a soft ball (in cold water).
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop up the chipped beef.
Mix all ingredients together with hands and form into a ball.

title: orange dream salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges into saucepan and add flour, sugar and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Add dry jello, stirring until dissolved.
Cool jello mixture and pour over oranges and marshmallow mixture.
Whip cream and fold into other mixture.
Refrigerate until solid.
This salad will be slightly less solid than regular jello salad.

title: chocolate cherry bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, nuts and chips.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, cherries and bananas.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
Add oil to very warm (but not hot) water.
Stir liquid into dry mix with a fork.
Shape into a ball.
You may spread dough in greased pan immediately, but it may work more easily if allowed to rest in a covered bowl for 15 to 20 minutes until it rises just slightly.

title: oyster corn
directions: Drain corn and add enough cream to juice of corn to make 1 cup. Melt margarine.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Pour in juice and cream to make sauce.
Add corn and eggs.
Layer oysters.
Cover with corn and crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Put in 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Cook over hot water 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 12 servings.

title: mama's stew
directions: Cut stew meat in bite-sized pieces.
Sprinkle with garlic. Roll in flour and brown in pan with oil.
When browned cover with water and stir really well, scraping bottom of pan to keep flour from sticking.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: *May substitute 1/2 cup applesauce for 1/2 cup oil.

title: turkey mushroom casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Saute mushrooms and peppers in butter. Sprinkle flour and stir. Add milk and bouillon and stir until thick. Add turkey, salt and pepper. Pour into pan and top with crumbs and cheese. Bake about 15 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Arrange in 2 layers in a greased baking dish.
Begin with beans.
Cover them with mushroom soup.
Add stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine tuna, soup, peas and milk in a casserole dish. Mix 3/4 cup chips in with other
ingredients. Sprinkle the remainder on top and bake 30 minutes.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Cook
sugar, cornstarch, pineapple and apricot jam over low heat and cool (set aside).

title: robbie's taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add rest of ingredients (undrained) and bring to a boil.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Mix well and bake in unbaked crust in oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: country apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar oil and eggs.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except hot grease; pour through funnel into hot grease and fry until brown.
Put on paper towel and put your favorite topping on it.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and onions into pieces.
Add crumbled bacon and sunflower nuts.
Blend together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Pour over broccoli mixture and toss.
Let stand overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: the best pot roast in the south
directions: Put roast, soup, season, vegetables and water in season bag; shake well.
Cook at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: friendship soup mix in a jar
directions: *Or other small pasta (can be put in a plastic sandwich bag to make it easier for the recipient to get out of jar).

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Add spices and sugar to cider, bring to boiling point and remove from heat. Let stand covered for 15 minutes and stain. Reheat, add fruit juice and ginger ale. Serve at once.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add chicken soup, onion, tomatoes, chili with beans and Tabasco sauce.
Alternate Doritos, meat and grated cheese (1 1/2 moons of Cheddar cheese).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy nacho dip
directions: Spread sour cream on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour salsa over sour cream and spread evenly.
Don't mix.
Sprinkle lettuce over salsa.
Place diced tomatoes on top of lettuce.
Cover with taco cheese.
Serve with nachos for dipping.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar, gradually.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add this to first mixture.
Heat milk. Add butter and then add to batter.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, melt chips, margarine and nuts.
Press half of crumb mixture firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: icy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, spices and ice cream until ice cream is softened.
Pile into pastry shell and freeze at least 4 hours. Top with whipped cream when serving.
Chocolate shavings or sprinkles make it more appealing to some children.
Enjoy this easy to make Thanksgiving treat any time of the year.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add sugar and butter; beat slightly.
Add corn meal.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add syrup and vanilla; mix well.
Pour 1/2 into each pie shell.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts over each pie.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: paula's peppermint ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough milk to finish filling your ice cream freezer container. Freeze.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: snow balls for christmas
directions: Dry olives well and cover with cream cheese to make ball. Roll in chopped walnuts.
Put in refrigerator and chill well. Slice in half lengthwise.
Arrange on plate in the shape of a fan.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling pot.
Mix onion, relish, mayonnaise and pepper liquid in large bowl.
Pour mixture over cooled potatoes; mix, then add boiled eggs.
I like to add salt and pepper to potatoes before adding other mixture.
Add more later as needed.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.

title: creamy chicken breast casserole
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish. Top each piece of chicken with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Cover with mixture of soup and wine. Top with stuffing mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Defrost bread.
Roll out jellyroll pan size.
Beat together eggs, garlic powder and oregano.
Spread 3/4 of egg mixture over bread.
Put layer of pepperoni over egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up like jellyroll and tuck ends in.
Slice in half and tuck in cut ends.
With remaining egg mixture, coat tops of loaves.
Prick tops with a fork.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine ketchup, sugar, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and mustard.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and 1/3 cup of ketchup mixture.
Mix well.

title: pickled beets
directions: Heat water, vinegar, sugar and spices to boiling.
Pour over beets.
Let set 6 hours.

title: oil salad dressing
directions: Pour 2 to 3 teaspoons boiling water over 3 garlic buds, cut up; let stand 10 minutes, then mix just this liquid with other ingredients.
Makes about 1 pint.

title: german chocolate pies(makes 2)
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Add milk, melted butter, coconut and nuts.
Pour into 2 large unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until firm.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Lay chicken out.
Put ham slice on top and then a slice of cheese.
Roll up and put in casserole dish.
Pour soup over all and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: With mixer, mix ingredients slowly for 10 minutes.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased Bundt pan.
To remaining 1/2, add Hershey's syrup and mix.
Pour over first half.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Place piece of aluminum foil over top of pan and bake for another 10 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Remove from pan.

title: baked apple pork chops
directions: Peel and slice apples to fill bottom of baking dish.
Add raisins and apple juice; top with cinnamon.
Trim pork chops and put celery salt and pepper on both sides before placing on apples. Top each chop with butter and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for medium chops or 1 hour and 20 minutes for thick chops.

title: perfect brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Blend in cocoa, vanilla and flour.
Flour and grease pan.
Bake at 325° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until done.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil and slice sweet potatoes and put in shallow pan. Make sauce of remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter; stir in nuts and sugar. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar melts and browns (8 to 10 minutes).

title: diner rice pudding
directions: Rinse medium saucepan with cold water.
Add milk and bring to a boil (medium heat).
Stir in rice and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender (55 minutes).
Combine sugar, cream, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Stir in this mixture and stir good; heat to boil.
Cover with cinnamon and raisins.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Season crawfish.
Melt butter in pot and saute crawfish for 5 minutes.
Remove crawfish.
Add all vegetables; saute for 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: saturday breakfast
directions: Let the children sleep late.
Take car to Mr. Burger.
Order the breakfast special.
Give check to husband.
Let someone else do the dishes.

title: cow pot
directions: Fry pork chops and cut into cubes.
Reserve 1/4 cup pan drippings.
Stir pork chops, pan drippings, cucumber, tomato, onion and banana pepper into cooked rice.
Mix well.
Serves 4.

title: nutmeg feather cake
directions: Cream shortenings and sugars; add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla. Bake in 2 greased, floured 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with chocolate icing.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.
Batter will be stiff.
Butter a black cast-iron, 10-inch frying pan.
Place batter in the pan and slash the top with a thin sharp knife in an "X" shape.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: jambalaya (shrimp)
directions: Can use two cans of Campbell's French onion soup.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger.
Mix together. Bake in slow oven 2 hours or more on low temperature.

title: fried mushroom nuggets
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry with a paper towel.
In a bowl blend the flour, garlic and club soda until smooth.
Dip mushrooms in batter and fry in about 1 inch of oil until golden brown. Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: hearty beer cheese soup
directions: Cook in covered pan the bouillon cubes, water, beer, celery and onion for 20 minutes. Add cream of chicken soup and cheese. Heat until melted and soup is hot. Freezes well.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients and pour in casserole.
Mash and bake the sweet potatoes if using fresh ones.
If using canned sweet potatoes, just mash.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Warm cream cheese to room temperature.
Break cream cheese into chunks.
Add eggs, milk, flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend with electric blender.
Slowly add sugar and blend until all is creamy smooth and even.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 1/2 hours until top part rises, turns brown and cracks open.

title: rotel
directions: Put all ingredients in a large enamel pan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into jars and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 7 pints.

title: brownies(indian heads)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
In a separate bowl, blend sugar and shortening; beat very well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients and blend (just until mixed).
Add vanilla and walnuts; blend just until mixed.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, ginger, mace, cloves, cinnamon and salt. Sift together.
Pour in pumpkin and mix well.
Beat egg, milk and butter and pour in the mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut over bottom of pan.
Prepare cake according to directions on box. Spread cake batter over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Spoon over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.
Cream cheese mixture works best when soft. Mixture has to be spooned over top of the cake.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil in pan.
Add cherry pie filling.
Bring to boil.
Pour over jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Cook cake layer in oblong pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together until creamy and place on top of cake layer.
Mix strawberries and glaze together.
Put on top of cake.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Place in tightly covered jars or containers and use as needed.

title: rhubarb meringue pie
directions: Cook rhubarb in very little water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, 1 1/3 cups sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat until very thick, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add the lemon rind. Beat egg yolks.
Add a little of the hot rhubarb mixture.
Cook about 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made with egg whites, pinch of salt and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 300°.

title: wassail
directions: Dissolve brown sugar in hot water.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Bring to boil.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 1/2 quarts.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello with fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Add peaches and nuts and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss, cover and chill.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine	all ingredients and mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until cookie tests done with a toothpick. Cool on cookie
sheet
about
minute
and
then remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: steak potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in the microwave until cooked.
Remove when done.
Slice in wedges.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add seasoned salt to taste.
Saute potatoes in skillet until crust forms. Remove and serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick so it won't stick.
Add bananas and cookies in bowl.
Pour pudding in.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into baking dish.
Brown beef, onion, etc., and pour over cabbage.
Pour rice over cabbage.
Add water to tomato soup.
Heat and pour over cabbage.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Fluff with fork before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 10 to 12 easily.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and chill overnight. Serve with assorted raw vegetables.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
Great on crackers.

title: split pea vegetable soup
directions: Combine peas and water.
Bring to boil in large kettle and simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for one hour or more.
Add ham bone or ham hocks, pepper and marjoram leaves.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 2 more hours.
Add onions, celery, carrots and salt.
Turn off heat and let soup stand for awhile.
Vegetables will be crispy.
If softer vegetables are desired, add to soup mix earlier in the cooking process.
Serve with crusty French bread and cheese.

title: frozen honey mousse
directions: On the top of double boiler, whisk yolks.
Beat in honey; place over simmering water and cook about 10 minutes.
Stir frequently; remove from heat and cool in refrigerator.
Whip whites with salt in separate bowl.
Whip cream in separate bowl; fold honey, yolks, cream and whites gently.
Spoon into glasses and freeze 4 hours.
Serve with melon slices.

title: oreo balls
directions: Mix together and roll in small balls.
Chill.
Roll in powdered sugar before serving.
Can be frozen.
If leftover after being rolled in powdered sugar, just freeze and re-roll before serving.

title: pot roast in red wine
directions: Remove fat.
Add wine, 3/4 cup beef broth and seasonings. Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Insert cloves in one onion and put all onions, carrots and potatoes in the pot.
Simmer 1 hour or until beef is tender.

title: easy corn souffle
directions: Boil corn and milk together for about 10 minutes.
Stir in butter, sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites stiff (not dry).
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: cucumber sandwich spread
directions: Grate cucumber, carefully press out moisture with paper towels.
Mix all ingredients well using enough mayonnaise to moisten so that filling will spread easily.
Spread on bread. Refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 20 servings.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Arrange peaches and almonds in pie shell.
Mix together remaining ingredients; pour over peaches.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°; reduce oven to 350° and continue baking 40 minutes longer, or until filling is set.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips until smooth and creamy. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips evenly on top of the batter, then sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350°
until done (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg lightly, combining with milk, and then add to dry ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Stir in melted butter.
Pour into pan greased with butter.
Sprinkle topping mixture over the batter.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: pasta with sauteed vegetables
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan. Add mushrooms. Cook 3 to 4 minutes. Add Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Add cauliflower, carrots and cooking wine. Stir occasionally.
When vegetables are done, serve over a bed of cooked noodles.

title: cheddar potato broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add onion; saute 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, water and bouillon cubes.
Cover and bring to boil; reduce heat and cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes. Remove 1 cup potato cubes and set aside.
Pour contents into large bowl and beat with mixer until smooth.
Return to pot.
Mix in reserved potatoes and broccoli.
Over medium heat gradually add cheese, stirring until heated through and cheese melts.
Season and enjoy.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Add pineapple. Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars and keep refrigerated.

title: orange or sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello. Add all ingredients. Let jell.

title: caramel rolls
directions: *One-half cup plus 2 1/2 teaspoons.

title: gloreo cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together until you can shape the dough into a smooth ball.
Let stand 20 minutes, loosely covered.
Form dough into marble-sized balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten each with a smooth bottom of a drinking glass, greased once, and dipped into Nestle Quik powder.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Remove at once from baking sheet to paper toweling, and immediately flatten each cookie with a smooth spatula.
Let cool 20 minutes.

title: pan coating mix
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Store in airtight container.
When needed, use pastry brush to apply to bottom and sides of baking pans.
No need to dust with flour.
This formula is used by many bakeries.

title: chicken and dressing hot dish
directions: Cook chicken in water with some onion and celery; reserve broth.
Put 2 or 3 cups cooked chicken in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Lay Swiss cheese over soup.
Mix Stove Top stuffing as directed on package, but add 1 cup chicken broth.
Put this on top of Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beverly's margaritas
directions: Put all ingredients together in a blender.
Fill with ice and blend.
Serve in salt rimmed glasses.
Garnish with lime slices. 4 servings.

title: cabbage casserole(brazil)
directions: Layer cooked cabbage leaves in baking dish.
Add layer of cooked ground beef.
Cover with 1/2 the white sauce, salt and pepper.
Repeat with second layer, covering with remaining white sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's red wine vinegar dressing
directions: Put all ingredients together in a bowl and with a mixer, blend and beat until thick and creamy.
Makes a delicious pink colored dressing.
It separates in the refrigerator, but just stir or shake and it is ready to use.

title: melita's mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and milk thoroughly and set aside. Reserving about 1 cup chips to sprinkle over the top, alternate the following evenly till all used: chips layer, chicken layer, pepper, onion, cheese slices, chips, chicken, pepper, onion, cheese, etc...After last ingredient is used pour soup mixture over the casserole ingredients. Sprinkle with remaining chips. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly and chips brown; about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Mix with spaghetti sauce.
Grate cheese.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Grease pan.
Place a layer of lasagne noodles in pan.
Cover with half of cheese.
Add a layer of sauce, then lasagne, cheese, sauce, lasagne and cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Cook (boil) chicken, let cool in broth.
Debone and cut chicken into pieces (save broth).
Make 1 package Stove Top stuffing.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 2/3 of stuffing.
Put chicken on top of stuffing.
Put Velveeta cheese on top of chicken.
Dilute cream of mushroom soup with chicken broth.
Pour over cheese.
Top it off with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lentil loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a well-oiled pan at 375° for 45 minutes.
Easy, healthy and a nice surprise for the family.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Crumble dried beef into the bottom of a baking dish.
Wrap each chicken breast with a bacon strip.
Arrange chicken breasts on layer of dried beef.
Mix sour cream with undiluted mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 275°.
Serve gravy over rice.

title: apple pie - french
directions: Preheat oven to 400°, put pie crust into a pie pan and crimp the edges.
Mix the apples, cinnamon, sugar, flour and water and pour into the pie pan.
Make the topping below:

title: 15 minute cookies
directions: Mix oats and peanut butter in a bowl.
Melt the sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk together.
Bring to just a boil.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla.
Pour over the oats and peanut butter.
Drop on wax paper.
Makes 3 or 4 dozen.

title: baked sliced beets
directions: Place beets into a greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients (except butter); stir and pour over beets.
Dot beets with butter.
Cover the dish.
Bake beets in a hot oven (400°) for about 30 minutes or until tender.

title: savory sirloin roast with gravy
directions: Place roast in Dutch oven or large baking pan.
Slice onion over roast.
Pour soups over roast, covering evenly.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes per pound or until meat is tender.

title: cinnamon nut cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients. Put dough on cookie sheet and pat out by hand. Spread over top 1 beaten egg white, then sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° until done. Cool and cut into squares.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and save juice. Pick out bones and skin and throw out. Break up salmon with fork and sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix all ingredients together including reserved juice. If mixture is too thin, add more bread crumbs. Put in greased loaf pan.

Bake in a water bath at 350. (In a larger pan than the loaf pan the fish is in. Fill with water and set the loaf pan with the salmon in it.) When brown on top and knife comes out clean, it's done. Let sit 15 minutes before turning out and cutting.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in butter.
Combine all other ingredients, except crab meat, in double boiler.
Heat until smooth, stirring often.
Add crab meat and sauteed vegetables. Blend and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serve hot with favorite crackers.
Can be used in chafing dish. Also, can be made ahead and baked when ready to use.
Add a few minutes to baking time for cold casserole.

title: split pea soup
directions: Heat olive oil in large, heavy soup pot over medium heat and saute onion and garlic until softened.
Stir in split peas, water, carrots, celery, bay leaf and black pepper.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Put all the ingredients on a sheet pan in the oven at 200°. Stir occasionally until all is melted.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Roll into crescent shapes and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar after cool.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat eggs and add corn.
Add milk, butter, salt, pepper and cornmeal.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: it's not a pizza dip
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and spread onto a large pizza pan or tray.
Top with the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with chips.

title: willetta's italian beef
directions: Put roast in pan and cover with water. Cook on top of stove for 2 hours. Remove from broth and cool. Slice thinly; remove fat and gristle and return to broth. Add beer and rest of spices. Simmer with lid on for 2 hours. Then simmer with lid off until liquid is cooked down and meat is completely broken up. Put meat on hard rolls (individual French loaves). Add a pepperoncini pepper and Mozzarella cheese (if desired) on each. Wrap in foil and heat at 250° until warmed through and cheese is melted or serve immediately.

title: broughton brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. On low speed, add dry ingredients.
After adding nuts, divide the batter.
Put melted chocolate squares in half on the batter only. Pour plain batter and then chocolate batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Run a knife blade through the batter to give marbleized look.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: down south barbecue
directions: Put half of onion in bottom of crock-pot, then add meat and other ingredients with remaining onion on top.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 12 hours.
Remove bone and fat from meat.
Put meat back in crock-pot.
Add onion and barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook an additional 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours on high, stirring 2 or 3 times. Serve from crock-pot on large buns.

title: cheddar cheese sticks
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter.
Add cheese and mix well, then add enough water to hold ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board to 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Fold corners into center.
Roll out again, dot with 2 tablespoons more butter; fold again.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for about 30 minutes.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
With pastry wheel, cut into scalloped strips 1/2 x 4 inches.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Add Cool Whip and stir with spoon.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: two-crust pumpkin pie
directions: Sprinkle flour on bottom of pie crust in plate.
Mix brown sugar, molasses, cinnamon and water.
Put pumpkin in crust. Spread sugar and molasses mixture on top of pumpkin and dot with small amount of butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and continue to bake 20 minutes more.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip.
Add pudding and mix slowly.
Add 2 cups milk while beating. Layer wafers, bananas and mix.

title: cyclops cookies
directions: In large bowl beat butter or margarine and peanut butter with electric mixer on medium speed about 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
With mixer on low speed, gradually add flour mixture to peanut butter mixture, beating well.
If necessary, cover and chill about 1 hour for easier handling.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and grease 2 cookie sheets.
In a medium bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl using an electric beater set on medium speed, beat together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Reduce mixer to low and gradually beat in the flour mixture, oats and zest.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonful onto the prepared cookie sheets spaced 2 inches apart.
Bake until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Transfer to a wire rack to cool.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Let the sheets cool before adding the next batch.
This will stop the cookies from spreading during baking.

title: divinity
directions: Bring to a boil, cook until mixture forms firm ball when a little is dropped in cold water.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff. Slowly pour boiling syrup in a fine stream over the egg whites, beating at high speed.
Beat until mixture passes glossy stage and holds its shape.

title: seafood souffle
directions: Butter 6 slices of bread on one side and place in dish, buttered side down.
Top with 1/2 cheese slices.
Cover with crabmeat and cooked shrimp.
Top with cheese and 6 more buttered bread slices, buttered side up.
Combine eggs, milk and spices. Pour over casserole.
Let stand 6 to 12 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chili-cheese tomatoes
directions: Cut each tomato into 3 large slices.
Squeeze gently to remove some seeds.
Combine sour cream, salt, pepper, sugar, flour, green onion and green chili.
Stir well.
Spoon over tomato slices. Sprinkle with cheese.
Just before serving, place in preheated broiler 4-inches from heat.
Broil until bubbly, about 4 minutes.

title: egg custard(without crust)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch pie plate and bake for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Melt butter in a 9-inch glass pie plate by covering with wax paper and microwaving 45 seconds, or until melted.
Stir cracker crumbs and sugar into butter; press mixture against sides and bottom of pie plate.
Microwave on High 1 minute, rotating after 30 seconds.

title: beef chow mein
directions: Brown the meat, onion and celery in the margarine (unless meat is very lean, omit margarine).
Add the remaining ingredients. Cover and cook in casserole in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ratatouille
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Put in a colander.
Sprinkle with salt and stir lightly.
Let stand for 30 to 40 minutes.
Rinse eggplant with cold water and drain well.
In a large skillet or cooking pot, saute onion in olive oil or defatted chicken broth.
Stir in peppers, zucchini, garlic, tomatoes, eggplant, basil, oregano, thyme, pepper and salt if desired.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: tart cherry salad
directions: Take all of the pineapple juice, juice of oranges and lemon and 1 cup sugar.
Bring to boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cherry jello.
Chill until partially set and add fruit and nuts.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop

Pick
out unpopped kernels.
Put
in	a large container.
In a microwave bowl, mix the
brown
sugar,
margarine,
Karo syrup and salt. Bring to a boil in microwave on High, then let boil 3 minutes. Remove from oven
and

Put mixture in a large brown

and put in microwave.	Cook on

Remove from oven and shake well, then return
to
