for 2 more minutes on High. Put in pan to cool.
Store in tightly sealed container to keep crisp for eating.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Crush Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use enough to cover bottom. Mix pudding according to package directions.
Spread on top of Oreos.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with more crushed Oreos. Chill.

title: crock-pot stuffed chicken
directions: Mix stuffing mix with 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook carrots 5 minutes. Drain.
Place carrots in bottom of crock-pot.
Stuff chicken with stuffing mix.
Close with poultry pins (lace shut). Sprinkle all over with salt and pepper to taste.
Place chicken in pot on top of carrots.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 7 hours. Remove and quickly brown in 400°
oven (preheated) 15 minutes prior to serving.
Good for quick after church dinner.

title: ants on a log
directions: Cut off the top of the bunch of celery.
Cut off the bottom too.
Pull apart the celery.
Wash the celery under cold water. Fill each "log" with cream cheese.
Put a few raisins on top of the cream cheese.
Cut up the logs and serve.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix with croutons in large bowl. Saute celery and onions in half of margarine; pour over croutons. Saute mushrooms in rest of margarine and add to croutons.
Add nuts and chicken broth to croutons.
Add sage if desired.
Stuff turkey.
Bake remaining stuffing in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: all american meat loaf
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; shape into two 7 1/2 x 4-inch loaves.
Place on lightly greased rack of broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Combine 1/2 cup catsup, 1 tablespoon horseradish and remaining ingredients and spoon over meat loaves. Return to oven and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings each.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Boil sugar, water, lemon juice, salt and pepper until sugar is dissolved.
Cool 20 minutes and pour over cabbage, carrots and celery.
Store in refrigerator in covered bowl.
Keeps crisp for several days.

title: heavenly dirt
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla until thick.
Add Cool Whip to cream cheese mixture and mix.
Add crushed cookies next.

title: baked rice
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Cook until rice is almost soft.
Remove from heat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon on top.
Bake 30 minutes in a small cake pan at 350°.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Combine cheese, sugar and water in pan.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple. Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Chill
until set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: veal cutlets with italian plum sauce
directions: Cook for 45 minutes on low flame with lid off; stir often. Pour over cutlets.
Be sure to remove basil leaves.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Grind oatmeal to a fine powder in food processor.
Mix together flour, oat powder, salt, baking soda and baking powder; add to creamed mixture and blend well.
(The mixture will be rather stiff.)
Grate Hershey bar and add with chocolate chips and nuts. Mix until evenly distributed.
Drop by tablespoons (1 1/2-inch balls) onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on wire rack.
Yield:
60 cookies.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain carrots.
Combine with the remainder of the ingredients. Marinate in the refrigerator overnight.

title: pina colada
directions: Before you start, sample the rum and check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now, go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc. and check the rum again for quality.
It must be just right!
Try it again.
With an electric mixer, beat one cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add one teaspoon of sugar and beat again. Meanwhile, make certain that the rum is the finest quality.
Add 2 large eggs and 2 cups of fried fruit and beat until very high.
If the fruit gets stuck in the beaters, just pry it loose with a screwdriver.
Sample the rum again, checking for consistency. Next, sift in 3 cups baking powder and a pinch of rum, 1 seaspoon toda and 1 cup pepper or salt.
Anyway, don't dret.
Just tample the rum again and mist in 1/2 pint of lemon juice.
Fold in chopped buttermilk and the strained nuts.
Tample the rum again.
Now 1 bablespoon srown buger or whatever color is available.
Mix well. Grease oven and curn on the take pan to 350°.
Pour the whole mess in the oven.
Cake tum rake out after mifty finutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and put in a greased casserole.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups grated cheese and 6 cups of crushed potato chips (10 ounces).
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: sherbet dip
directions: Combine equal amounts of mayonnaise and your favorite fruit sherbet.
Attractively arrange fresh fruits of your choice on a large platter surrounding a small bowl of either of the dips. Suggested fruits are:
seedless grapes, strawberries (fresh, hulled), orange slices (peeled), pineapple chunks, apple wedges, banana slices, mandarin orange slices, melon balls or chunks.
Be sure to dip fruits that darken in orange juice before placing on tray.

title: southern red rice casserole
directions: Brown sliced sausage in bacon drippings.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Crumble fried bacon into ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pop-a-shroom(stuffed mushrooms)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Clean mushrooms and remove stems, saving half of them.
Set aside caps.
In a nonstick skillet, lightly saute onion and chopped mushroom stems in butter until onion is soft.
Stir in bacon and bread.
Remove skillet from heat, then stir in cheese.
Stuff caps.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet and bake for approximately 15 minutes.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Mix together and pour over contents in pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Dip pieces of boned chicken into melted butter, then into flour seasoned with salt.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Butter casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) and place rice on bottom.
Place ham on next and top with chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream together; beat and pour over chicken.
Place Swiss cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: cherry hill chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix soup and mayonnaise.
Blend well (use a wire whisk if you have one).
Add celery and water chestnuts.
Butter lightly a 3-quart glass Pyrex casserole.
Put in chicken and cover with the other mixed ingredients.
Mix the dry stuffing mix with the melted butter.
Layer the stuffing on the casserole.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
If made early in the day, it needs extra time.
Feeds about 6.

title: banana split pie
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick oleo.
Spread in cake pan or pie.

title: corn custard
directions: Grease baking dish.
In mixing bowl, add beaten eggs to creamed corn.
Add margarine, salt and sugar.
Now add half of milk and stir until blended.
Now add your cornstarch to the milk left. Stir until this dissolves, then add to dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: braised lamb shanks(with tomato sauce)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Lightly coat lamb shanks with oil. Arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: dirt dessert(cookies and cream)
directions: Put half the crushed Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and margarine.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix juice, thawed orange juice, thawed lemonade and lemon juice.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour into large punch bowl. Add 7-Up or soda and liquid if using.
Decorate with sliced fruit and serve.

title: german cinnamon cookies
directions: Process hazelnuts, almonds, granulated sugar, almond paste, lemon and orange peel, cinnamon and salt in a food processor until finely ground. Add egg whites and process, pulsing until dough begins to clump and come together, about 30 seconds.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt margarine with chocolate, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.

Lightly beat until mixed. Stir in flour and nuts. Spread batter into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake 30 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack. When cool, glaze top or sprinkle sifted powdered sugar over top. Chocolate glaze (optional).

title: quick pineapple-lime pie
directions: Mix milk, drained pineapple, lime juice and food coloring. Fill pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and grate chocolate shavings over top.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: dish pan cookies
directions: Cream well the first 5 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients. If dough is very stiff, add a small amount of milk.
Should be dry, but hold together.
Roll in small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large bowl add the can of plum tomatoes.
Squish it up.
Dice the pepper and onion, then add to the tomatoes.
Sprinkle in basil and salt to taste.
Cut up all of the potatoes.

title: corncob jelly
directions: Break cobs.
Put cobs in boiling water for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Strain to make 3 cups.
Add the Sure-Jell and bring to a rolling boil again.
Add the sugar.
Boil 5 more minutes or to jelly stage.

title: orange julips
directions: Mix all in blender.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble toasted bread in baking dish.
Beat eggs, sugar and milk.
Pour this over the bread and let set for 30 minutes.
Bake until set and golden brown.
Make a Creamy Cinnamon Sauce to pour over pudding when done.

title: exotic salad
directions: Toss all together and serve on lettuce.
If you like a more Polynesian flavor, add 1 tablespoon curry powder and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.

title: halibut royale
directions: In a shallow dish, combine the lemon juice, salt and paprika. Add halibut steaks and marinate 1 hour, turning steaks after 30 minutes. Cook chopped onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Place steaks in greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Top with 6 green pepper strips and sprinkle with onion. Bake at 450° about 10 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Rinse the dry cobs to get rid of any leftover chaff.
Boil for 30 minutes rather gently.
Remove from heat.
Strain through white cloth.
Measure to get 3 cups juice if necessary.
Add water to get that amount.
Add powdered pectin and bring to a full rolling boil.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Bring to boil again.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes until it starts to gel when you lift out spoon. This might be as little as 1 minute.
Skim; pour into sterilized glasses and seal.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 pints.

title: micro turkey au gratin
directions: In 1 3/4-quart casserole, combine green pepper, onion and water.
Cook covered 2 to 3 minutes until tender.
Stir in milk, uncooked rice, soup, poultry seasoning and 1/4 cup cheese.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle
remaining cheese while hot.

title: squirrel with gravy
directions: Cut squirrels into pieces.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Cover with water in cooker and cook until tender.
Add water as needed to make enough broth for gravy to cover cooked squirrel.
Remove squirrel from cooked broth water.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup cold water.
Pour into boiling broth.
Cook until thickened.
Put squirrel back into gravy.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: easy dessert
directions: Mix well and put in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate and butterscotch chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: deep-fried halibut
directions: Blend dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix eggs, milk and oil and add to dry ingredients.
Thaw fish if frozen and dry thoroughly.
Coat with flour, then dip in batter.
Fry in 1-inch of oil in skillet.

title: pepperoni cheese dip
directions: Heat 2 hours on high in crock-pot.
Serve with torn-up bread pieces.

title: mamaw's cherry delight
directions: Combine the butter and graham cracker crumbs.
This makes pie shell for cake pan.

title: crock pot potatoes
directions: Melt margarine, sour cream and cheddar cheese soup in a medium saucepan.
Combine with cooked potatoes in crockpot.
Heat on low for 1 hour.
Top with chives and bacon bits.

title: baked breaded eggplant
directions: Wash and slice eggplant.
Sprinkle with onion salt, garlic and pepper.
Beat egg and milk; dip eggplant slices in mix.
Put slices on piece of foil.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Place slices in baking dish and bake at 375° to 400° until brown.
Good and easy.
Serves 4 easily.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients; heat and stir until it can not be stirred any longer.
Cool and knead until you reach the consistency of play dough.
Store in a plastic bag or covered container.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Prepare with taco seasoning as directed on package.
In a large bowl, cut or shred lettuce. Add chopped tomatoes, kidney beans and olives.
Mix well; add meat mixture.
Mix well.
Add grated cheese and crushed Doritos.
Do this a little at a time to keep cheese from sticking and to mix well.
Serve warm or chilled.
Top with taco sauce or favorite dressing.
Great plain.

title: chicken and dressing combo
directions: Boil chicken; pick meat off bones.
Save 2 cups of chicken broth.
With mixer, mix cream of chicken, cream of celery soup and the 2 cups of chicken broth.
In another bowl, place dressing mix and melt margarine.
Mix together real well, saving a few crumbs of dressing mix for the very top.
Layer in baking dish, chicken, dressing mix and soup mixture.
Add crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "best ever" cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves.
Mix well.
Chill in lightly oiled ring mold.
Unmold to serve.
Fill center with preserves.
Serve with crackers.
Can prepare day before.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and powdered sugar.
Put 1 cup cracker crumbs on bottom of pan, then add creamed mixture.
Add nuts, then whipped
cream.
Top with remaining crumbs.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind onions and peppers to make 3 cups.
Add to ground zucchini.
Cover with ice water and salt; let stand 1 hour. Combine sugar, vinegar, water, celery seed and turmeric in saucepan and boil 3 minutes for syrup.
Drain zucchini mixture and rinse under running cold water; drain.
Add to syrup mixture and cook 15 minutes.
Put into jars while hot and seal.
Very good on hamburgers and hot dogs.

title: french fried turnips
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge turnips in flour mixture. Deep fry in vegetable oil until brown.
Drain turnips on paper towel.

title: elk or deer roast
directions: Cut roast into serving size chunks; pour soup and wine in crock-pot.
Add onions and seasonings to your taste.
Mix well and add meat.
Cook on low 6 hours or on high 3 hours until done.

title: peach schnapps fizzes
directions: In a blender, blend ice cream and 1/2 cup sliced peaches until smooth, but still thick.
Pour into 2 chilled stemmed glasses. Add Schnapps and club soda and garnish with additional peach slices.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap
a
slice	of
bacon
around
each chicken breast. Sprinkle
with chipped beef in a casserole dish.
Place breast on beef.
Mix soup, sour cream and pour over chicken.	Bake at 275° for 3 hours uncovered.
Serve over rice.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add nutmeg.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes longer.

title: peter pan cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter; mix well.
Add granulated sugar; mix.
Add brown sugar and mix slowly until creamy.
Add beaten eggs and milk and mix well.
Sift flour and baking soda, then add to mixture, blending well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Flatten each cookie with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, cherries, marshmallows, nuts and coconut.
Then add 1/2 pint Cool Whip.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter, chocolate and milk in large heavy saucepan and cook, stirring only until sugar and chocolate are melted.
Cook until a little dropped into cold water forms a soft ball (238°).
Remove from fire and when almost cold, add vanilla and beat until fudge loses its glossy appearance and is firm enough to hold its shape when a little is dropped from the spoon.
Stir in nuts, and turn into greased pan.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Arrange spinach on serving plate.
Add mushrooms and vegetables.
In nonstick frying pan, saute chicken pieces in salad dressing just until cooked, 5 to 8 minutes.
Spoon over spinach and drizzle with pan juices.
Add a few herbed croutons on top.

title: easy caramel apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients well (except pecans).
Pour into a 9-inch regular frozen pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecan pieces. Bake at 375° on preheated baking sheet for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit for fried pies
directions: Wash, peel and cut up fruit.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Then pour over fruit and allow to stand overnight.
Cook fruit until tender and juice is thick.

title: cream cheese puffs(great for brunch)
directions: Remove crusts of bread and roll flat with rolling pin.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolk and sugar.
Spread thinly on bread slices. Roll up each slice and cut in thirds.
Dip in 1/2 pound melted butter, then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(These are sooooo good!)

title: baked tomatoes
directions: You will need a small baking pan.

title: spinach and artichoke hearts
directions: Cook spinach and drain; mix in artichoke hearts, butter, sour cream and most of cheese.
Pour in baking dish where butter was melted; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage creole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Shred cabbage into large pan. Add soup, tomatoes and Ro-Tel.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix all and cook 1 hour or longer.

title: peanut butter sauce for ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Stir constantly over low heat until smooth and creamy.
Serve warm over ice cream. Makes about 1 cup.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and add cinnamon.
Continue to add soft butter, milk and egg yolks.
Beat whites from the 4 eggs; fold into the mixture, not having the egg whites too dry.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells, stirring all the time so the spices will not settle.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 375° and bake 30 minutes longer or until pie seems firm.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Will also need 5 clear plastic cups.

title: delicious spinach salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix raspberry vinegar, salt, sugar, poppy seed, dry mustard, minced onion and oil; set aside.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter and oleo in a medium saucepan.
Add vanilla; mix in sugar.
Put into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and place in refrigerator until hard.
Cut into servings of choice.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and chopped nuts. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.

title: cream cheese and green chili sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: champagne wine delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container; chill and serve. Garnish with orange slices.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake.

title: cheese - strawberry ring
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight. Shape into ring.
Fill center with preserves.
Serve with Ritz crackers.
Delicious!

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage until done, drain and mix in mustard, pepper, garlic powder, onion soup mix & cream cheese.
Rinse and chop sauerkraut into finer pieces.
Add sauerkraut into mixture and cover.
Let mixture cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: sauteed apples and raisins
directions: Cut apples in half and then into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Melt margarine in a large skillet; add apples.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 6 to 7 minutes or until almost tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; add to skillet.
Add brown sugar and raisins; bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; stir in lemon juice.
Serve warm.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices. Sprinkle with salt. Saut onions, tomatoes, paprika, pepper and spices. Add meat; cook 5 minutes. Rinse eggplant. Place alternate layers of meat mixture and eggplant in casserole dish, beginning and ending with meat. Cover with foil and bake 40 minutes at 350°. Remove foil and sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: texas baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add onion, milk, both soups and Ro-Tel.
Bring to a boil for a minute.
Layer the tortillas, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° in oven for 30 minutes.

title: old south oatmeal pancakes
directions: Put oats in bowl; add milk. Stir and let cool. Beat egg yolks, butter and oat mixture.
Sift flour, salt, sugar and baking powder together and add to oat mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. If too thick, add a little milk.
Pour onto hot griddle by spoonfuls.

title: baked eggplant parmesan
directions: Pare eggplant and cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Beat egg and lemon juice together.
Dip eggplant slices in egg and lemon juice, then roll lightly in bread crumbs.
Saute garlic in oil for 5 minutes.
Add eggplant slices and saute for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove eggplant and keep hot.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, soup, onion and mayonnaise.
Put in oblong baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes very thin.
Coat in flour, meal, salt and pepper mixture.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Umm Umm Good.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Add flour, sugar, salt, soda and spices.
Beat well.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake for 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion in olive oil.
Add minced garlic and ground chuck. Chop fine.
Add salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Brown well. Drain.
In separate pot, cook tomatoes, tomato sauce, paste and soup.
Add generous amount Italian seasoning mix, meat and tomato mixture and cook with finely chopped pepperoni.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: mitzi's caramel apple pies
directions: Combine and cook on low until well mixed.
Pour into 2 deep crusts or 3 regular pie crust shells (unbaked).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned.

title: easy dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together using water; mix until thin.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Can be made at night and put in a large sealed container in refrigerator until ready to bake.

title: sloppy joe burgers
directions: Brown ground beef, pepper and onion together.
Drain well. Add chili sauce and beans.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, until hot. Serve on hamburger bun.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix well and serve on lettuce cup.
Refrigerate.

title: sallet fixins
directions: Wash greens and put in a pot.
Cover with water.
Cook in about 2 quarts of water.
Add bacon, salt and pepper. Cover and cook on medium heat until tender.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hearty chicken noodle soup
directions: Place all ingredients except egg noodles into a large pot. Cover with water.
Bring to a slow simmer, then cover.
Simmer for about 1 hour or until chicken is cooked (if you used raw chicken). Then add egg noodles and 3/4 cup water.
Cook until noodles are done.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 large bowls of soup.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil, with mixer.
While mixing at medium speed, add oil in fine stream.

title: shish kebab
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Form the meat into individual ovals.
Place in a Teflon pan (round).
Add 1/2 cup of water and cook on low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Burn 1 piece of charcoal and put it in the middle of the pan.
Add two drops of water to the charcoal to create a flame.
Cover it quickly for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: scallops mornay
directions: Saute onions in butter for a few minutes.
Add scallops, wine and garlic.
After several minutes, add the mushrooms.
Cook just until scallops are done.
Remove from heat and pour juice off, saving 1/2 cup of the liquid, discard remaining.
I put scallops and vegetables in pan with a lid to keep warm.
Add 1/2 cup half and half to the reserved liquid.
In saucepan melt 2 tablespoons butter and add 2 tablespoon flour until smooth.
Slowly add cream mixture, blending constantly.
Cook until thick, then add Parmesan cheese.

title: pineapple ice
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth, about 5 seconds.
Pour into metal refrigerator tray or or loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches. Freeze until firm around edges, but soft in center, about 2 hours.
Spoon into blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth. Pour into tray.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into patties.
Fry in hot oil until done.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Place flank steaks in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Score lightly on both sides.
Sprinkle both sides with Accent.
Combine all other ingredients and pour mixture over the flank steak.
Marinate overnight for best flavor (or at least 4 hours).
For best taste, prepare on your outside grill (prepare as you would any other steak).
Serve sliced very thin.

title: quick vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onion in one teaspoon oil in large skillet or pot.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook rice while chili is simmering.
Complimentary proteins (rice and beans equals complete protein without meat).
Also high fiber source.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chuck wagon bean casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Saute 1/2 chopped onion and bell pepper until cooked thoroughly.
Add to first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring once.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter both sides of bread and place in single layer in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water in saucepan until tender. Deskin and debone and chop in small pieces.
Chop onion and shred cheese.
In another saucepan heat soup, green chiles, sour cream and salsa.
Add as much salsa as you like depending on how spicy you want it.
Add 2 cups of chicken broth (left from cooking chicken) to mixture.
Soften corn tortillas in warm vegetable oil. Pat off excess oil.
Layer in 15 x 10 x 2-inch Pyrex dish:
soup mixture, 6 tortillas, chicken, onion, soup and cheese.
Repeat. Heat at 350°
until bubbly, approximately 45 minutes.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: You will need 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan or cookie sheet or short-sided pan with same area.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix melted oleo with chocolate cake mix.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cherry-banana pie
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple in separate cups.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add cornstarch, salt, vanilla, food coloring and sugar in saucepan.
Add cherries and pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Let cool completely.
Add bananas and pecans.
Put into your favorite crust; top with whipped cream.
Chill.

title: quick meal soup and casserole(two meal dish)
directions: In a medium pot, cook chicken, covered with water.
When done, add vegetables and cook until they are tender.
Set broth and vegetables in refrigerator.
Take chicken out and let cool.
When chicken is cool, cut in serving size pieces.
Reserve small pieces for soup.
Brush large pieces with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle Romano cheese on top of mayonnaise; sprinkle with oregano.
Broil for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve with salad and potatoes.
Enjoy!

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool.
Spread top with strawberry preserves.
Chill.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix gelatins with hot water.
Cool to early jell stage.
Mix milk, cheese, pineapple, lemon juice, nuts and celery.
Add to gelatin and mix.
Mold in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "microwave" corn bread taco bake
directions: Microwave Directions:
Crumble ground beef into 8 x 12-inch microwave-safe dish.
Cook, covered, on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until beef is cooked.
Stir beef halfway through cooking time. Drain well.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions; stir in 1/2 can onions.
Spoon muffin batter around edge of beef mixture.
Cook, uncovered, on Medium (50% to 60%) for 7 to 9 minutes or until corn bread is nearly done.
Rotate dish halfway through cooking time.
Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions; cook, uncovered, on High for 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
(Bread will finish baking during standing time.)

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender and cool.
Mix soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, pepper and salt in small sauce pan.
Bring to a boil.
Layer carrots, onions, and bell pepper in large bowl.
Pour hot soup mixture over layered vegetables, refrigerate overnight. Will keep two weeks if kept in refrigerator.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add quart of milk; cook on low heat until it starts to thicken.
Beat eggs; when mixture starts to thicken, pour slowly into eggs.
Return to stove and cook until it coats spoon.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and Pet milk. Pour in freezer and fill to within 2 inches of top of canister with milk or Pet milk.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Combine sugar and 6 cups water in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then cool.
Add everything but 7-Up and strawberries; freeze.
Soften to slush.
Spoon into punch bowl.
Add 7-Up and strawberries.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter together in top of double boiler.
Spread on waxed paper-covered cookie sheet.
Melt in microwave the semi-sweet chocolate, 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Pour the chocolate on top of the other mixture and swirl with knife.
Refrigerate, and when cold, break into chunks.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix in flour and salt.
Stir in vanilla, apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into pound cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 to 90 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; add diced apples.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; add to apple mixture and mix thoroughly.
This will be a thick batter.
Add nuts; mix again.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch square pan or a loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Test cake with a toothpick.
Run knife around edge to loosen; remove from pan to cool.*

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Drain the chilies and save the juice.
Grate half of the cheese onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle drained chilies on top of cheese; spread remaining cheese over chilies. Beat the eggs with chili juice and pour over the cheese.
Sprinkle top with paprika (just enough for color).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine all fruits and nuts in large bowl. Sift over them some of the flour combined with spices.
Toss to coat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour-spice mixture to first creamed mixture alternately with honey and soda.
Combine with fruit and nut mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased pan. Decorate with pineapple slices and bake in 275° oven for about one and one-half hours.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Do not open stove door on your cake.

title: egg rolls
directions: Bring celery and cabbage to boil.
Drain.
Cook shrimp and pork in fat 4 minutes.
Add celery and cabbage.
Add soy sauce, chestnuts, green onion and garlic.
Cook 6 minutes.
Roll in skins and fry.
Serve with Sweet and Sour Sauce.

title: chorizo con queso
directions: In one large skillet, fry chorizo.
In another large skillet, scramble eggs.
When done, combine in a large pan.
Add peppers. onion and garlic.
Cook until warm.
Wrap in flour tortilla and enjoy.
You may add jalapeno peppers if you wish it to be hotter.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix well and bake in a well oiled loaf pan 1 1/2 hours at 225° or 250°.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to hamburger.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: banana disaster
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.

Prepare graham cracker crumbs and press into a 1 1/2 to 2-quart shallow baking dish. Spread butter, sugar, egg and vanilla mixture over crust, then spread pineapple over mixture, then bananas, then Cool Whip. Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Let set overnight or for at least 6 to 8 hours.
No cooking needed.

title: cheese soup
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat all day or at least 4 to 5 hours.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly greased a 12-cup muffin tin. In a large mixing bowl, stir together sugar, salt, allspice, cinnamon, baking soda and flour.

title: haman taschen(israel)
directions: Grind raisins, apricots
and
prunes;
mix with coconut and jam.
Set aside.
Cream the butter, sugar and eggs together;
beat in the
vanilla.
Sift
the
flour and baking powder and add to creamed
mixture, working in thoroughly.
Roll out. Cut into squares.
Place
a	scant
tablespoon
of filling and fold into 3-cornered	shape.	Place
on
greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 50 squares.

title: peas and eggs
directions: Put oil, onions and parsley in frypan.
Cook until onions become soft (do not overcook onions).
Spread onions on bottom of frypan.
Spread peas over onions, saving juice.
After peas are added, make 4 wells.
Put two eggs in each well.
Add pea juice (which was drained) around edges of pan.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on top.
Simmer, covered, for
1 hour or until eggs are firm.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Combine ketchup, bourbon and sugar.
Mix well.
Add hot dogs and stir.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: orange french toast
directions: Combine eggs, 1/4 cup powdered sugar, cinnamon, orange rind and juice in a shallow pan.
Stir well.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Cook first 4 ingredients to a boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add soda.
Whip well and pour over corn.
Scatter corn onto a greased cookie sheet; bake 1 hour. Stir it after 30 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in bowl.	Cut in 3/4 c. butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press mixture evenly into greased 13 x 9 inch pan, using a piece of plastic wrap to press firmly in pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 17 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: quick pecan sweet rolls
directions: Melt margarine in an 8-inch round layer pan.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Arrange biscuits in pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Invert pan on a serving plate.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing pan, to allow sticky mixture to drop over biscuits.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand or
use a mixer. Use a tablespoon to drop on cookie sheet. Take a fork to flatten lightly. Bake 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring quart of milk to boil; add rice to milk and keep stirring until it boils.
In a 2-quart baking dish, beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Then pour milk mixture into the egg mixture mixing well.
Bake in hot 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: hot chicken salad deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes and almonds.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with corn flakes and almonds.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly after each addition.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add rolled oats, coconut or raisins and Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just thawed.
Drain well.
Layer half of broccoli in a round greased casserole dish. Spread one can of soup, half of onion flakes, half of cheese and salt and pepper. Repeat and sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, 3/4 teaspoon of salt, milk, baking soda, cream-style corn and bacon drippings; set aside.
Saute ground chuck and add salt to taste.
Drain meat on paper towels to absorb grease.
Keep the onion, Cheddar cheese and jalapeno peppers separate.
Grease and heat a large, black skillet.
Sprinkle with cornmeal and let brown slightly.
Pour half of cornmeal-egg mixture in skillet.
Sprinkle the cheese evenly over mixture. Spread meat on top.
Place chopped onion on top, then place peppers.
Pour remaining cornmeal-egg mixture over top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Shape into small balls with spoon.
Fry in deep fat until well browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 6.

title: granola
directions: Mix ingredients well and add liquid to dry ingredients.
Mix and bake at 250°.
Stir every 20 minutes.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: marinated green bean salad
directions: Clean beans.
Pinch ends, but leave long.
Cook about 12 minutes until they are tender, but not overcooked.
Drain. Refrigerate.
Just before serving, pour dressing over the beans and onion.
Add more salt if necessary.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Soften margarine.
Add the sugars, then add vanilla and eggs. Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto
cookie
sheet.
Bake about 8 minutes in a 350° oven.	Yields 5 dozen.

title: zucchini squash loaf
directions: In mixing bowl beat together the zucchini, sugar and egg.
Add oil and mix well.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, etc. and stir into zucchini mixture.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly on rack.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.

title: no-fat fruit dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Good dip for any type of fruit.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare buns by putting mustard and mayo on buns.
Put a Kraft single on one side with slice of onion.
Put a heaping spoonful tuna on the other side.
Close bun; place on baking sheet.
Bake until cheese is well melted, about 20 minutes. May leave off onion.
Add fries and it's a great meal.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Take chicken, spread salt, pepper and dressing over chicken. Place in oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Saute onion and celery in small amount of cooking oil.
Drain and set aside.
Steam carrots.
Add carrots, milk, soups and mushrooms to onion and celery.
Stir and heat through.
Add frozen peas.
Stir.
Remove chicken from oven after 1 hour.
Allow to cool 30 minutes.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Lay chicken into buttered casserole dishes, 9 x 12 x 2-inch and 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Pour soup mixture over the chicken.
Unfold pie crust; place on top of pie and flute edges.
Place in 350° oven and heat 30 minutes.
If crust is not brown, turn oven up to 400° and watch carefully.

title: hot jelly spread(must prepare 24 hours in advance)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cream cheese, thoroughly and let blend for 24 hours before using.
Serve over cream cheese brick with crackers of choice.
I like Triscuits.

title: deluxe fajita nachos
directions: In a medium skillet, combine Chicken, Fajita Seasoning, Water; blend well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
In a large shallow oven proof platter, arrange chips.
Top with Chicken and Cheeses.
Place under broiler to melt cheese.
Top with Tomato, Olives, Green Onions, and desired amount to Salsa.
Serve with Guacamole and Sour Cream.

title: lemon eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk; set aside until thick, then add dry lemon jello and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Place layer of crackers (unbroken) in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour a layer of pudding mixture over crackers. Continue layering until you end with a layer of crackers. Carefully spread frosting over crackers. Refrigerate for 24 hours for best flavor.

title: venison roast
directions: Take a sharp knife and stick holes in the roast and stuff each hole with a sliver of garlic.
The holes should be about 1 1/2 to 2-inches apart like a pork roast.
Then rub the roast with lots of salt and pepper.
Flour it generously.
Put in your Dutch oven with 1/8-inch grease and fry until golden brown on all sides.
Put on the lid and cook very slowly until tender.
No vegetables except potatoes, if you want them.
The meat should make its own juice, but if it doesn't, add a touch of white wine.
Never add water to venison roast.

title: fantastic chicken
directions: Mix
barbecue
sauce
with
equal
amount of water in a large skillet or electric frying pan.
Add the frozen chicken. Cover and
turn
on high.
After chicken has thawed, separate the pieces and reduce heat, maintaining a bubbly boil.	About 15 minutes before dinner, uncover and allow sauce to thicken. Serve sauce
over
chicken.
Cook
1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Place in a 1 qt. casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with wheat crackers or Melba toast rounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in casserole and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add combined flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by level measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crispy cookies, or 20 to 30 minutes for burnt cookies, HA HA.
Just kidding.
Cool for 2 minutes on cookie sheet, then remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Beat butter for 45 seconds.
Add granulated sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add almond flavoring and 2 teaspoons water.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Shape into balls, fingers or crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes.
Do not brown!
Cool slightly.
Shake gently in a bag with powdered sugar.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together until well combined.
This works best in food processor.
Place in oven-safe dish and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: pineapple creme dessert
directions: Mix half the pineapple with the gelatin in a small saucepan. Let stand 2 minutes.
Separate the eggs.
Combine the yolks with the pineapple and the gelatin.
Stir until blended.
Cook over moderately high heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add remaining pineapple to mixture.
Whip egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar until stiff peaks, like for meringue, are formed.
Fold egg whites into cooled pineapple mixture.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Pour the pineapple creme into 4 dessert dishes.
Cover and chill until set, about 4 hours.
Garnish with sprigs of mint or lemon leaves and a slice of pineapple.

title: rigatoni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic salt.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and pepper (to taste).
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in bowl the cottage cheese, milk and salt.
Add rigatoni and toss to coat well. Spoon 1/2 of rigatoni into baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella and 1/2 of the sauce.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: different salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in hot water.
While still hot, dissolve jello.
Cool.
Add applesauce.
Put half of mixture in mold.
Let congeal.
Whip cream, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread over congealed mixture; let harden.
Add rest of mixture and chill. Serve.

title: herb rice
directions: Toast uncooked rice in a 1 1/2-quart covered dish for 20 minutes at 400°.
Mix broth and water and bring to a boil.
Add margarine to rice and stir well.
Add broth to the rice and return to oven for an additional 20 minutes or until broth is absorbed. Remove from oven and add soy sauce, onions and herbs.
Stir until mixed well.
Great served hot or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients (except 1/2 of the croutons). Spoon into
lightly
greased 3-quart casserole dish. Top with the remaining croutons.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aztec stew
directions: When meat and potatoes are done, add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini-carrot cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. In a food processor with the S blade in place, use the pulse control to grind the hazelnuts to a mealy consistency. (You want 1 1/2 cups of ground hazelnuts when you're done and for some inexplicable reason, they seem to actually grow a little rather than shrink a little when you grind them.) Set the ground hazelnuts aside. In a large mixing bowl, whisk the eggs until well blended. Add the oil, yogurt, ground hazelnuts, protein powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg, mixing well after each addition. (It's especially important that the baking soda be well distributed through the mixture.) Add the zucchini and carrots last, mixing well. Thoroughly coat a ring mold or Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray and turn the batter into it.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Slice both packages in half placing both "bottoms" in 13 x 9 pan. Spread with mixture of Grey Poupon, butter, onion powder and Worcestershire.
Put ham and cheese on top, then roll "tops" in mixture of melted butter and poppy seeds. Put foil on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (until cheese melts). Watch time.

title: sweet onion cake
directions: In heavy skillet, melt 4 tablespoons butter or oleo and saute onions until slightly crisp, but not brown.
Cool.
Cream sugar with 1/4 cup Crisco.
Beat until fluffy. Add eggs, beat slowly. Add flour mixture, stir until combined.
Add milk.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add onions.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans or deep (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake 30 minutes for round pans and 40 minutes for large pan at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop stems into pieces. Brown sausage, onion and stem pieces together.
Drain grease.
Add cream cheese in pieces.
Cover for a couple of minutes to soften cheese.
Stir in bread crumbs to blend ingredients.
Stuff mushroom caps with heaping teaspoon of stuffing.
Pat to compact together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes or microwave on High 5 minutes at a time until tender.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add and mix together vanilla and eggs.
Add sifted flour and milk, adding a little bit of these ingredients at a time.
Stir and mix well after each addition.
Mix together hot water and cocoa.
Add to cake mixture. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seafood over angel hair pasta
directions: In 12-inch pan, heat Italian dressing; cook shallots over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Add carrots and snow peas and cook 2 minutes.
Add broth, then sherry.
Bring to a boil, then add shrimp, scallops and mussels.
Simmer, covered, for 3 minutes or until seafood is done and mussel shells open.
(Discard any unopened shells.)

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Boil margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour this over the flour sugar mixture and beat 2 minutes. Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 17-inch pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While still warm, frost with:

title: pineapple-pear salad
directions: Place pineapple slices on bed of lettuce; add pear half.
Fill center of pear with cottage cheese, mayonnaise or something of your choice.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery seed, celery, onion, salt substitute and pepper.
Dice eggs and add to potato mixture.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard.
Chill several hours before serving.
Best if made 24 hours ahead.

title: pilgrim chicken
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, butter, brown sugar and pineapple in bowl; mix well.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour cranberry mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: delicious meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine ground beef, soup mix, eggs, catsup, bread crumbs and water.
Shape into loaf and place into baking pans.
Bake about 45 minutes or until done in a 375° oven.
Serves 8.

title: original reese cup recipe
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and peanut butter. Roll into balls; then flatten. Dip in chocolate coating.

title: peach cooler
directions: Put all ingredients, except ice cream, in blender.
Liquify until smooth.
Add ice cream and blend (1 cycle).

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Put the canned sweet potatoes in a buttered casserole.
Take the liquid, add juice or water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until clear and pour over potatoes.
Bake in oven until heated through.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat juice to mix jello. Let cool and add chilled 7-Up. Chill this and then add rest of ingredients.

title: squash and stuffing
directions: Cook squash; mash and drain.
Mix with half of stuffing mix, pimentos, onion, sour
cream and carrots.
Place in large casserole.
Melt butter and
mix
with remaining stuffing mix. Place on top of squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gourmet duck
directions: Soak large duck 4 hours in sherry or other sweet wine.
Season inside of duck with salt and pepper.
Stuff loosely with favorite dressing.
Salt and pepper outside of duck.
Place each duck on double thickness of foil.
Spread generous amount of orange marmalade on each duck and wrap tight in foil.
Cook on open baking sheets at 325° for 3 hours.
Turn back foil and brush with mixture of butter, syrup and Kitchen Bouquet.
Return to oven with foil turned back.
Bake 30 more minutes or until browned.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Mix 1 cup milk with cornmeal.
Scald 3 cups milk in top of double boiler.
Add hot milk to cornmeal mixture, then cook in top of double boiler about 10 minutes or until mixture is consistency of thin mush.
Add baking powder, salt and butter.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix together and store in tightly covered container. Use 3 tablespoons (to taste) per cup of hot water.

title: baked crab au gratin
directions: Mix egg and mayonnaise together well.
Add the next 5 ingredients to the mix and fold in crab meat.
Place in casserole and bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes or until it is firm to the touch in the center.
For two.

title: white clam sauce
directions: About
30 minutes before serving:
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
In
quart
saucepan
over medium heat, in hot olive oil
and butter or margarine, cook garlic until lightly browned. Add
parsley
and
reserved
clam
liquid; over high heat,	heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10
minutes
to blend flavors.
Add clams and cook until clams are heated through, stirring occasionally.
Add salt to taste. Makes about 3 cups sauce.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Add ingredients.
Dot butter over bread crumbs.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour covered.

title: manicotti
directions: In a large pan, brown meat and drain fat.
Add water, tomato paste, onions, mushroom, 2 tablespoons parsley, oregano, salt, sugar and garlic.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add chili and soup.
Thaw tortillas so they will come apart; dip them in sauce and line bottom of a dish with half of them.
Add 1/2 of meat mixture; sprinkle meat, onion and cheese in layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gelatin poke cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin as directed on package.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut meat into small cubes and brown in oil.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until lightly browned.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer gently 40 to 45 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes and water to cover vegetables. Cook 20 to 30 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, orange juice, poppy seed and sugar in bowl; stir.
Gently toss spinach and strawberries together.
Drizzle poppy seed mixture over spinach and strawberries per serving.

title: french meat dressing
directions: Cook all ingredients in a frying pan until bubbly.
Serve as a side dish or as turkey stuffing (let cool before stuffing turkey). Stuffs a 5 to 6 pound turkey.
Add 2 pounds ground beef to double recipe.

title: cheese soup(8 servings)
directions: Combine water, bouillon, celery, onion and potatoes in a heavy pan; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add noodles, vegetables, soup and cheese.
Simmer on low heat until cheese is melted and soup is thoroughly heated.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cut cheese into small cubes.
Chop eggs.
Crumble 3 crackers into bottom of a buttered casserole.
Over the crumbs put a layer of cheese, a layer of eggs, a layer of asparagus and a little mushroom soup.
Dot with butter but do not salt.
Alternate layers until all ingredients are used.
Add milk and 3 teaspoons asparagus liquid.
Sprinkle extra crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bacon-cornmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin cups.
Stir together cornmeal, flour and sugar, if desired, in mixing bowl.
Combine buttermilk and oil together and add to dry ingredients, stirring until blended.
Stir in crumbled bacon.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, filling each 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 med. muffins.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce and cheese.
Toss in a large bowl slowly adding dressing and cheese; garnish with croutons.

title: lemon cheese bundt cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine the margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs, 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar.
Mix on low speed until blended.
Repeat until all ingredients are blended. Add extracts and blend well.
Pour batter into a prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for one hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: apple rolls
directions: Put 1 1/2
cups
sugar	in pan with 2 cups water.
Heat until sugar
dissolves.
Mix
all ingredients together.
Roll out
thin. Spread
with
oleo.
Cover
with
diced	apples. Sprinkle with nutmeg, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up into a big roll.
Slice
off about 1-inch thick.
Put in sugar water and bake in hot 375° or 400° oven for about an hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a large bowl in same order as written. Refrigerate.
Will stay crispy for 3 or 4 days.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups and rice together in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place pieces of fryer on top and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with bay leaf with skins on until tender; set aside until cool and peel and shred.

title: chicken in orange sauce
directions: Place chicken breast halves in a shallow 1-quart casserole. Arrange onion slices over each piece.
Combine the next 5 ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 25 to 30 additional minutes, or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally with sauce. Sprinkle with paprika; garnish with orange slices.
Yields 2 servings.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and make into patties.
Brown on both sides. Combine soup, milk and Kitchen Bouquet.
Pour over meat patties. Simmer, covered, for 1/2 to 1 hour until done. Spoon gravy over meat occasionally.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook spinach as directed and drain.
Cook shells as directed and drain.
Mix shells with spinach.
To this mixture, add the beaten eggs, oil, bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger in frying pan.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, and desired amount of rice to hamburger.
Will probably need to add some water to mixture so rice can cook.
Stir and cook mixture until rice and zucchini are
tender.
Top mixture with shredded cheese and let melt.
Serve warm.
Can also top with sour cream.

title: microwave spaghetti sauce
directions: Place ground beef, mushrooms, onion and garlic in microwave-safe dish and cook on High for 8 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Into meat mixture add tomatoes and liquid, sugar, tomato paste, salt and Italian seasoning.
Cover and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce power to Medium and cook 10 more minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over pasta.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°. When done, put 1 1/2 cups miniature marshmallows on top and return to oven until melted.
Let cool and top with 1 pound powdered sugar, 1/2 cup evaporated milk, 2 tablespoons butter and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Bring milk and butter to boil; pour over cocoa and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over cool cake.

title: frozen chicken sandwiches
directions: Fill buttered slices of bread with mixture.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
To serve, beat 4 eggs and 2 tablespoons milk together. Crush potato chips.
Dip frozen sandwiches into egg mix, then in crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Delicious!

title: apple prune sauce
directions: Cook apples with the water until tender. Add rest of ingredients (except Equal) and cook until heated through. Remove from heat and cool. Add the Equal and stir. Refrigerate in covered jar. Will keep 2-3 weeks in refrigerator. Good served with ham and beef.

title: glazed ham balls
directions: Mix chopped onion and ham loaf together; form 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place balls in shallow baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over ham balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, basting occasionally with the glaze.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter a cookie sheet.
Boil the sugar, water and corn syrup together until a long thread spins from the spoon and the mixture turns light brown.
Add the peanuts and heat to boiling again, cooking until the mixture turns a brownish gold.
Add the soda, vanilla and margarine.
Stir and pour onto the buttered pan. Spread it out as thin as possible.
After it hardens and cools, break it into pieces.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least one hour.
Serves 4. Equals 1 protein, 1 fruit and 15 optional calories.

title: chili stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft. In large pan, brown meat and drain. Stir in corn, tomatoes, ketchup, pepper and chili powder. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Slice potatoes and spoon mixture over each potato. Garnish with sour cream, grated cheese and green onions if you want to.

title: skillet ham and potatoes
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until lightly browned, stirring occasionally. Combine flour, mustard and milk in a small bowl.
Mix with fork until well blended.
Stir milk mixture and ham into potatoes. Cook until mixture thickens, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat. Simmer for 5 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken pieces, soup, milk and sour cream.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Mix stuffing, broth and melted margarine and spread over chicken in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked 9-inch pie shell at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine lettuce, spinach and sprouts.
Pour boiling water over carrots and peas and allow them to blanch for 1 to 2 minutes. Drain.
Add chicken, peas and carrots to salad greens.

title: easy cucumber pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with water.
Let stand 6 or 7 days.
Pour off water.
Rinse good and slice.
Add alum.
Cover with water and let stand 6 hours.
Pour off and rinse.
Cover with white vinegar and let stand 6 hours.
Pour off.
Add sugar and pickling spice (tied in a bag).
Don't put any vinegar in it.
Let stand in jar for 30 days.
Put in jar and process for 10 minutes.

title: tomato fideo dinner
directions: Season steak generously with salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok or large skillet over medium-high heat; cook steak in it about 3 to 4 minutes or until browned and no longer pink, stirring frequently. Remove form pan. Keep warm. Add remaining oil, broken pasta and garlic to pan. Carefully toss pasta in oil to coat; cook until pasta is golden brown, stirring constantly. Stir in tomato sauce until well blended. Cover; reduce heat to low. Cook about 10 minutes or until pasta is tender. Combine steak and broccoli with pasta; toss all together. Cover and cook on low until heated through. Serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Heat
applesauce
until
warm.	Add raspberry jello and stir until completely dissolved.
Add Sprite and orange juice. Chill and serve.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; warm over stove.
Place in a chafing dish (to keep warm).
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry streusel squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray; lightly flour.

title: chocolate nut brittle
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Butter the foil and line with saltine crackers.
Boil sugar and butter.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate bits and pour over crust.
Top with chopped walnuts.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: chili rellenos(serves 20)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Clean and seed Ortega chilies.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Line greased large lasagna pan with 1/2 of the chilies.
Add 1/2 of the cheese.
Layer other 1/2 of the chilies; cover with remaining cheese.
Beat together the rest of the ingredients, except tomato sauce; pour over top.
Put in oven. When bubbly, lower oven to 350° for 25 minutes.
Spread the tomato sauce over top; bake another 15 minutes.
Serve, refrigerate or freeze.
Bring to room temperature.
Heat in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lasagne supreme
directions: Core, trim and shred cabbage.
Trim and thinly slice squash. In a large skillet, saute cabbage for 10 minutes in hot oil.
Add squash and cook an additional 10 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: linzer square(austrian)
directions: Mix all ingredients as for pastry.
Roll between sheets of wax paper (or press).
Line bottom of jelly roll pan with dough.
Save some for lattice.
Spread dough with jam and nuts and then make lattice over top with reserved dough.
Brush with egg and then bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: pork chops, southern style
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in their own fat.
Cover with sliced vegetables.
Mix the next 5 ingredients and sprinkle over vegetables.
Add tomato juice.
Cover and bake 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.

title: brussels sprouts with bacon and caraway
directions: Cook bacon in microwave or on stovetop until crisp.
Cool, crumble and set aside.
Prepare brussels sprouts by cutting off outside leaves, and making an x in the top of the core.
Add 2 Tbsp. water in a covered casserole dish with sprouts, and cook in microwave for 6 minutes, or until tender.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
In a saucepan, bring vinegar and brown sugar to a boil.
Pour over brussels sprouts.
Sprinkle caraway seeds and bacon on top to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in greased baking dish (spray Pam works).
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and lemon pepper seasoning.
Mix well.
Spread over broccoli and chicken.
Mix margarine and bread crumbs together and sprinkle on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook for 5 minutes the Karo, brown sugar, oleo and salt.
Take off stove, add soda.
Stir good.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir very good.
Bake in oven at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix the 1 tablespoon lemon juice and egg.
Mix the 1/4 cup flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip the chicken in the lemon juice and egg mixture, then into the flour mixture.
Saute in the margarine.
Mix the bouillon, boiling water and 4 tablespoons lemon juice.
Add the chicken.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir 1 tablespoon flour into sauce after removing breasts.
Serve over rice.

title: southern cucumber sandwiches
directions: Slice cucumbers thin and stand in bowl of vinegar and water for 30 minutes, room temperature; drain well.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder, onion salt and Worcestershire. Cut bread slices in 2-inch rounds, spread lightly with cream cheese mixture.
Top with cucumber slice shortly before serving. Garnish with stuffed olive or paprika or both.
Makes about 45.

title: men only meat loaf
directions: Add hamburg and sausage in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Place into a baking dish.
Meat loaf should be about 3 inches thick.
Lightly cover with ketchup.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar with margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, creaming after each addition until light in color.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add extracts.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° to 350° for about 15 minutes, or until done.

title: calico beans(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
May simmer on top of stove until flavors blend if you are in a hurry.
May also add Kolbasi (optional).

title: fast and easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown your ground beef and drain.
Cream potatoes.
In a casserole dish, put ground beef in the bottom of dish.
Open can of creamed corn and put over ground beef (cold) not heated.
Put mashed potatoes on top.
Ready to serve.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix ingredients, then add tomatoes and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell and bake.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add pizza sauce and tomato sauce.

Cook noodles approximately 6 to 7 minutes and then drain. Grease pan with butter and then layer ingredients, half of the noodles, then half of meat mixture, sprinkle with half of the cheese and pepperoni, then repeat with noodles, meat, cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is browned.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion and cheese with eggplant. Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole (I used long flat glass dish).
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle rice evenly into casserole dish.
Arrange chicken on top of rice.
Mix soups and water and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
To serve:
Mound rice in center of plate surrounded by chicken pieces.
Garnish with parsley.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan; add onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add mushrooms.
Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Mix soups, turkey, celery and onion mixture and chicken broth.
When noodles are done, mix in with the turkey mixture.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese to top.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: lomien - fast and easy
directions: Any leftover veggies will do.
Have a 1/2 cup at least.

title: pecan pie (no fail)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Filling may seem a little soft in middle, but will set as it cools.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add the Jell-O gelatin (any flavor) until dissolved into mixture.

title: gina's taco salad
directions: Toss together ingredients.
Leave chips and dressing until you are ready to serve, otherwise chips become soggy.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Chop vegetables fine.
Mix with salt and sugar.
Put spices in cheesecloth bag.
Simmer in vinegar for 30 minutes.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, remove bag of spices and heat to boiling point.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and sugars and mix well.
Add nuts and oatmeal.
Form into rolls and chill overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mother's angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift into a mixing bowl the flour.
Cut in margarine and oil. Dissolve in water the yeast and sugar.
Add to flour mixture, then add buttermilk.
Work together with a large spoon until all flour is moistened.
Cover bowl and store in refrigerator.
When ready to use, take out amount desired.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or brown in a 400° oven.
This recipe makes 3 dozen light flaky biscuits.
The dough will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: rocket chili
directions: Brown and crumble meat.
Combine in
large crock pot and cook on low setting for 3-5 hours.
